1
00:00:04,720 --> 00:00:07,620
The first thing I noticed that morning was the silence.

2
00:00:08,240 --> 00:00:10,200
Not the silence of the vaults I knew.

3
00:00:10,700 --> 00:00:13,880
Dance, calculated, built to hide things.

4
00:00:14,360 --> 00:00:15,540
It was the good kind.

5
00:00:16,020 --> 00:00:19,200
The  kind  that  only  exists  in  rooms  where  someone  sleeps  in

6
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:19,820
peace.

7
00:00:20,220 --> 00:00:22,540
Noelia breathed slowly beside me.

8
00:00:22,720 --> 00:00:24,560
Her hand curled up near her chin.

9
00:00:24,960 --> 00:00:28,360
The way she'd slept ever since she'd started sharing the bed with me.

10
00:00:28,620 --> 00:00:29,460
Three months.

11
00:00:30,040 --> 00:00:31,040
I was still counting.

12
00:00:31,580 --> 00:00:33,280
I got up without making a sound.

13
00:00:33,280 --> 00:00:36,340
The  penthouse  had  thin  blinds  that  filtered  the  light

14
00:00:36,340 --> 00:00:37,320
off  Lake  Michigan.

15
00:00:37,860 --> 00:00:40,140
And cast pale patches across the sheets.

16
00:00:40,660 --> 00:00:44,040
Long and quiet like fingers of light that didn't want to wake anyone.

17
00:00:44,460 --> 00:00:46,900
I stood there for a second just to look at her.

18
00:00:47,040 --> 00:00:49,320
Her chest rose and fell.

19
00:00:49,780 --> 00:00:51,380
No tension in her shoulders.

20
00:00:52,080 --> 00:00:53,580
No glinch in her jaw.

21
00:00:54,160 --> 00:00:57,180
I'd  seen  Oelia  sleep  restlessly,  dreaming  about

22
00:00:57,180 --> 00:00:57,700
the  altar,

23
00:00:58,120 --> 00:01:01,360
about  Calvin,  about  the  big  screen  that  showed  my

24
00:01:01,360 --> 00:01:01,780
face.

25
00:01:01,780 --> 00:01:03,020
Not that morning.

26
00:01:03,460 --> 00:01:04,800
It was domesticity.

27
00:01:05,120 --> 00:01:07,600
That was the word I'd never had a reason to learn.

28
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:10,280
And now it turned up all the time.

29
00:01:10,720 --> 00:01:12,280
Stuck to the smallest things.

30
00:01:12,700 --> 00:01:16,380
I put my shirt on in silence, rolled the sleeves to my elbows,

31
00:01:16,860 --> 00:01:17,880
and went to the kitchen.

32
00:01:18,460 --> 00:01:24,680
The coffee brood quick with that strong smell that took over the whole hallway on cold days.

33
00:01:25,100 --> 00:01:28,120
I used the chance to set the sugar bowl beside her cup.

34
00:01:28,440 --> 00:01:29,560
The way she liked it.

35
00:01:29,940 --> 00:01:31,140
Spoon already inside.

36
00:01:31,140 --> 00:01:35,600
It was ridiculous how much attention I paid to small things.

37
00:01:36,020 --> 00:01:40,160
Before her, I didn't even know there was a right position for a sugar bowl.

38
00:01:40,620 --> 00:01:42,280
Daria was waiting for me downstairs.

39
00:01:42,840 --> 00:01:46,100
I saw the car parked in the private garage when I came down.

40
00:01:46,480 --> 00:01:46,860
Armored.

41
00:01:47,280 --> 00:01:47,620
Black.

42
00:01:48,160 --> 00:01:52,420
The window opened just enough for him to see me and tighten his expression by two millimeters.

43
00:01:53,060 --> 00:01:54,700
His way of saying good morning.

44
00:01:55,060 --> 00:01:55,300
Coffee?

45
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:56,400
I asked.

46
00:01:56,980 --> 00:01:58,080
Already had some.

47
00:01:58,080 --> 00:01:58,860
Lair.

48
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:03,200
Strange definition of a lie for someone who only asked a question.

49
00:02:03,720 --> 00:02:05,120
I got into the passenger seat.

50
00:02:05,660 --> 00:02:06,600
The meeting was early.

51
00:02:07,020 --> 00:02:10,220
The casino's annex office was 20 minutes from the penthouse,

52
00:02:10,600 --> 00:02:12,800
and Masimo had confirmed the night before.

53
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:19,020
For weeks I'd been negotiating the transfer of two casino operations to entirely legal management.

54
00:02:19,620 --> 00:02:23,500
Every signed paper was a crack I put in what I'd inherited from my father.

55
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:24,840
It wasn't fast.

56
00:02:25,080 --> 00:02:25,960
It wasn't comfortable.

57
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:31,700
But it was the only thing that felt coherent since Noelia had agreed to sleep at my side.

58
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,660
Does she know you're going to the casino?

59
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:36,660
Daria asked as the garage gate rose.

60
00:02:37,140 --> 00:02:38,160
I looked out the window.

61
00:02:38,700 --> 00:02:44,400
The street was still damp with cold, black puddles reflecting the street lights that hadn't gone off yet.

62
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:45,960
I said a regular meeting.

63
00:02:46,440 --> 00:02:47,280
He didn't answer.

64
00:02:47,760 --> 00:02:49,280
It was worse than if he had.

65
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:54,300
I knew Daria's silence is well enough to tell which frequency each one weighed on.

66
00:02:54,300 --> 00:02:56,500
That one weighed on disapproval.

67
00:02:57,060 --> 00:02:59,740
I'd promised her on the balcony her hand in mine.

68
00:03:00,260 --> 00:03:01,520
That I wouldn't lie anymore.

69
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:04,080
And there I was, three months later,

70
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:08,220
shaving the truth around the edges just so I wouldn't worry her.

71
00:03:08,380 --> 00:03:09,460
It was a micro-ly.

72
00:03:09,860 --> 00:03:10,680
It was harmless.

73
00:03:11,260 --> 00:03:14,720
It was exactly the kind of thing I'd sworn I would never do again.

74
00:03:15,020 --> 00:03:17,120
I clenched my jaw and looked ahead.

75
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:21,340
The casino's annex office had the discretion only old money buys.

76
00:03:21,340 --> 00:03:27,660
Dark oak walls, low lamps, the thick carpet that muffled the sound of your own foot steps,

77
00:03:28,140 --> 00:03:31,260
and the round table my father had made before he died.

78
00:03:32,100 --> 00:03:35,760
Massimo was already seated in the same brown suit as always,

79
00:03:36,140 --> 00:03:39,920
and the smile of a man who felt at home in any room I walked into.

80
00:03:40,300 --> 00:03:43,320
He'd brought Dolcey from the Italian bakery in the neighborhood,

81
00:03:43,880 --> 00:03:46,340
wrapped in wax paper that still held warmth.

82
00:03:46,780 --> 00:03:49,340
He pushed the bundle toward me when he saw me arrive.

83
00:03:49,340 --> 00:03:51,720
Eat son, your thin.

84
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:53,340
I haven't lost weight.

85
00:03:53,880 --> 00:03:55,100
Your mother called yesterday.

86
00:03:55,740 --> 00:03:56,400
Said your thin.

87
00:03:56,900 --> 00:03:58,260
I believe her more than a mirror.

88
00:03:58,800 --> 00:03:59,300
I sat.

89
00:03:59,940 --> 00:04:01,940
Dario stayed standing against the door.

90
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:03,660
Shoulder against the frame.

91
00:04:04,260 --> 00:04:06,980
Watching with that stillness that made everyone uncomfortable,

92
00:04:07,620 --> 00:04:08,440
except me.

93
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:10,340
The meeting lasted two hours.

94
00:04:10,980 --> 00:04:13,620
Massimo questioned, with calculated gentleness,

95
00:04:14,300 --> 00:04:18,140
the speed at which I'd been legalizing the operations he said he understood,

96
00:04:18,140 --> 00:04:23,420
that he respected it, that he saw in me the same courage he'd seen in my father,

97
00:04:23,980 --> 00:04:27,160
but that slow was better, that the market spooked easily,

98
00:04:27,720 --> 00:04:31,500
that man loyal to me might feel betrayed if the transition was abrupt.

99
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:34,460
Every word of his came wrapped in affection.

100
00:04:35,080 --> 00:04:37,020
That was how he always spoke to me.

101
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:39,640
That was how he'd spoken to me my whole life.

102
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:43,080
I nodded at several points, disagreed at a few.

103
00:04:43,460 --> 00:04:47,800
When I left the room, the hallway was cold and smelled of the coffee no one had drunk.

104
00:04:48,140 --> 00:04:50,700
And Dario caught up to me before I reached the door.

105
00:04:51,180 --> 00:04:52,060
You trust him.

106
00:04:52,420 --> 00:04:53,400
It wasn't a question.

107
00:04:53,940 --> 00:04:54,760
He raised me.

108
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:55,360
I answered.

109
00:04:55,980 --> 00:04:57,160
That's not what I asked.

110
00:04:57,640 --> 00:04:58,440
I didn't answer.

111
00:04:58,920 --> 00:04:59,860
I got in the car.

112
00:05:00,340 --> 00:05:01,360
I checked the clock.

113
00:05:01,940 --> 00:05:05,000
Our still left before the end of Noelia's shift at the hotel,

114
00:05:05,460 --> 00:05:08,440
but the urge to have lunch with her had come out of nowhere and stayed.

115
00:05:08,940 --> 00:05:10,920
I told Dario to drive over there.

116
00:05:11,180 --> 00:05:13,540
I texted to let her know I was on my way,

117
00:05:13,780 --> 00:05:16,080
that I'd brought hunger and nothing else.

118
00:05:16,080 --> 00:05:18,880
She replied with an emoji I couldn't describe,

119
00:05:19,440 --> 00:05:21,860
but it made me smile alone in the backseat.

120
00:05:22,300 --> 00:05:26,340
The hotel still had that clean morning smell when I came in through the service door.

121
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:28,900
Marble, flowers changed early.

122
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:31,160
The faint trace of floor wax.

123
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:33,480
I took the internal elevator up.

124
00:05:33,880 --> 00:05:37,220
When the door is opened on the floor of the old vaults, I stopped.

125
00:05:37,760 --> 00:05:41,660
There was a maintenance crew in the hallway, a ladder leaning against the wall.

126
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:44,980
A broken seal on one of the dark steel doors.

127
00:05:44,980 --> 00:05:49,780
The ceiling light flickered faintly as if the whole floor were waking up along with

128
00:05:49,780 --> 00:05:51,500
whatever had been kept in there.

129
00:05:51,740 --> 00:05:53,100
The door was open.

130
00:05:53,640 --> 00:05:54,620
I knew that door.

131
00:05:55,100 --> 00:05:57,120
It was one of the oldest vaults in the building,

132
00:05:57,400 --> 00:06:02,440
from the days when the hotel still served as a private vault for city families who didn't trust banks.

133
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:06,420
No one was authorized to open anything there without three signatures.

134
00:06:06,980 --> 00:06:09,600
I looked at the badge on the chest of the nearest employee,

135
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:11,260
who authorized the opening.

136
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:13,440
He looked at me, hesitated.

137
00:06:13,440 --> 00:06:16,500
The events manager sir, Miss Cross.

138
00:06:17,180 --> 00:06:18,520
I walked toward the vault room.

139
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:21,100
The hallway seemed longer than it had ever been.

140
00:06:21,540 --> 00:06:24,700
As if each step I took added another half meter to the distance.

141
00:06:25,280 --> 00:06:27,640
I'd felt this exact sensation before.

142
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:31,720
The sensation of arriving too late to something I didn't know was happening.

143
00:06:32,220 --> 00:06:37,500
When I turned the corner, I saw noelia standing near a little table pushed against the wall.

144
00:06:37,980 --> 00:06:39,320
Sorai was beside her.

145
00:06:39,640 --> 00:06:42,040
Holding a yellowed paper envelope in both hands,

146
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:45,380
careful the way someone holds something that might break apart.

147
00:06:45,940 --> 00:06:49,700
And on top of the table, an old tape machine turned slowly.

148
00:06:50,220 --> 00:06:53,240
The tape running between two worn plastic reels.

149
00:06:53,960 --> 00:06:55,440
A voice came out of the machine.

150
00:06:55,940 --> 00:06:58,200
It was the voice of a man I didn't know,

151
00:06:58,540 --> 00:07:00,560
but I recognized the surname he spoke.

152
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:02,100
It was mine.

153
00:07:02,340 --> 00:07:04,540
The dust smelled of old paper and damp metal.

154
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:06,580
That was the smell of the vault floor.

155
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:09,460
And I'd already been there three times that week.

156
00:07:09,460 --> 00:07:13,540
Always with the renovation plans in my hand and my head somewhere else.

157
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:16,640
The last thing I expected was to find something real.

158
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:18,580
This is the last one.

159
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:22,020
Sorai said, tapping the steel door with the tip of her clipboard.

160
00:07:22,540 --> 00:07:25,200
If a literal skeleton shows up inside this vault,

161
00:07:25,640 --> 00:07:26,660
I swear I'm quitting.

162
00:07:27,220 --> 00:07:28,320
I laughed half-heartedly.

163
00:07:28,940 --> 00:07:32,460
It was one of those polite laughs, just so I wouldn't ruin my friend's joke.

164
00:07:33,100 --> 00:07:35,860
Sorai was the only person who still made me laugh before coffee.

165
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:38,500
And I knew she could tell when the laugh came out hollow.

166
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:40,360
She didn't call me on it.

167
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:43,160
It was the kind of friendship that doesn't need explaining to work.

168
00:07:43,640 --> 00:07:44,840
The employee turned the wheel.

169
00:07:45,300 --> 00:07:48,460
The door opened with a groan that sounded like years choked up.

170
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:52,300
Metal contracted by time, resisting until the last second.

171
00:07:52,780 --> 00:07:54,020
Inside there was dust.

172
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:55,440
Three yellowed folders.

173
00:07:56,140 --> 00:07:58,680
A large cassette tape inside a little plastic case.

174
00:07:59,020 --> 00:07:59,640
And an envelope.

175
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:01,940
It was the envelope that stopped me.

176
00:08:02,180 --> 00:08:03,760
There was a name typed on the front.

177
00:08:04,220 --> 00:08:05,140
And taro cross.

178
00:08:05,140 --> 00:08:08,540
I felt my blood dropped to somewhere it wasn't supposed to be.

179
00:08:08,700 --> 00:08:09,920
I stood still too long.

180
00:08:10,420 --> 00:08:11,700
The metal smell got stronger.

181
00:08:12,340 --> 00:08:13,560
Or I got more motionless.

182
00:08:14,020 --> 00:08:14,920
I couldn't tell which.

183
00:08:15,860 --> 00:08:16,980
Sorai looked at the envelope.

184
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:18,260
Looked at me.

185
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:20,300
And stopped joking in the same breath.

186
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:21,980
No way?

187
00:08:22,840 --> 00:08:23,960
That's my father's name.

188
00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:25,960
She picked up the envelope without asking.

189
00:08:26,480 --> 00:08:27,460
I picked up the tape.

190
00:08:27,900 --> 00:08:30,760
There was a label stuck to the side of the case with a date on it.

191
00:08:30,980 --> 00:08:32,360
A date from before I was born.

192
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:33,820
My hands were shaking.

193
00:08:33,820 --> 00:08:35,600
I told myself they weren't.

194
00:08:36,040 --> 00:08:37,080
And I looked at them.

195
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,920
And they kept shaking just the same.

196
00:08:39,380 --> 00:08:41,460
Completely ignoring what I thought about the matter.

197
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:43,780
There was an old machine in the room next door.

198
00:08:44,160 --> 00:08:45,940
One of the kind that still used tape.

199
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:48,360
It had belonged to the hotel's previous director.

200
00:08:48,860 --> 00:08:50,540
And had never been taken off the desk.

201
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:53,960
Forgotten between papers and an astray no one used anymore.

202
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:56,200
I carried the tape over there without thinking.

203
00:08:56,860 --> 00:08:57,560
Sorai followed.

204
00:08:58,040 --> 00:08:59,680
Quiet for the first time in years.

205
00:09:00,180 --> 00:09:01,380
I slotted it in.

206
00:09:01,560 --> 00:09:02,420
I pressed the button.

207
00:09:02,420 --> 00:09:03,680
The tape rast.

208
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:05,520
Then came a long hiss.

209
00:09:06,100 --> 00:09:06,820
And then the voice.

210
00:09:07,320 --> 00:09:08,900
You know who I am, Mr. Melvani.

211
00:09:09,480 --> 00:09:10,980
I'd never heard that adult voice.

212
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:13,240
I'd heard his voice calling me to breakfast.

213
00:09:13,980 --> 00:09:15,460
Reading a children's book out loud.

214
00:09:16,040 --> 00:09:19,620
Singing happy birthday with the wrong lyrics because he thought the right ones were boring.

215
00:09:20,180 --> 00:09:23,220
I'd never heard my father's voice being the voice of a man at risk.

216
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:24,420
But it was him.

217
00:09:24,860 --> 00:09:29,040
It was him the same way the echo of my own voice on the answering machine was me.

218
00:09:29,620 --> 00:09:31,280
Unmustakable even without a name.

219
00:09:31,280 --> 00:09:32,900
Even without context.

220
00:09:33,580 --> 00:09:35,380
I came because my family was threatened.

221
00:09:35,940 --> 00:09:38,240
He was saying his voice too firm.

222
00:09:38,620 --> 00:09:41,080
Like someone who'd rehearsed before walking into the room.

223
00:09:41,580 --> 00:09:44,800
And because you're the only man in this city who can make that threat small.

224
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:46,300
Another voice answered.

225
00:09:46,900 --> 00:09:49,360
Old, patient, with a heavy accent.

226
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:51,880
And the kind of calm that doesn't come from kindness.

227
00:09:52,380 --> 00:09:53,560
It asked for three names.

228
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:55,440
My father gave the three names.

229
00:09:55,920 --> 00:09:56,880
I pressed the pause button.

230
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:58,120
I pressed it wrong.

231
00:09:58,680 --> 00:09:59,580
The tape kept going.

232
00:09:59,580 --> 00:10:00,900
They went back to the beginning.

233
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:02,320
I heard it again.

234
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:03,680
I didn't hear it better.

235
00:10:04,100 --> 00:10:04,900
I heard it worse.

236
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:08,520
Because the second time I already knew what was coming and I listened anyway.

237
00:10:09,040 --> 00:10:10,660
Unable to prepare myself for anything.

238
00:10:11,060 --> 00:10:12,300
I felt a hand on my shoulder.

239
00:10:12,920 --> 00:10:15,480
And it took me half a second to understand it was surreye.

240
00:10:15,860 --> 00:10:16,940
She didn't say anything.

241
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:18,540
She was just there.

242
00:10:18,920 --> 00:10:20,520
The weight of her hand in the right place.

243
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:22,380
The way a true friend stays.

244
00:10:22,920 --> 00:10:24,720
When there's no word that fixes it.

245
00:10:24,940 --> 00:10:27,360
That was when I noticed the third body in the room.

246
00:10:27,620 --> 00:10:28,760
I lifted my eyes.

247
00:10:28,760 --> 00:10:30,800
Everin was standing in the doorway.

248
00:10:31,560 --> 00:10:33,520
White shirt with the sleeves rolled to his elbows.

249
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:35,940
His broad shoulders filling the frame.

250
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:38,160
Hand braised on the side of the door.

251
00:10:38,680 --> 00:10:39,580
Eyes on me first.

252
00:10:40,140 --> 00:10:41,180
On surreye after.

253
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:42,640
On the machine last.

254
00:10:43,160 --> 00:10:45,220
I saw the second he understood what was playing.

255
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:46,820
I saw his jaw lock.

256
00:10:47,220 --> 00:10:50,360
I saw the way a man holds his breath without knowing he's held it.

257
00:10:50,580 --> 00:10:52,880
For three months I'd set his surname like a caress.

258
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:55,080
I'd laughed at him when he signed papers.

259
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:58,260
I'd whispered against his neck in the kitchen while the coffee brewed.

260
00:10:58,260 --> 00:11:01,940
I'd completely forgotten what that surname was capable of doing.

261
00:11:02,480 --> 00:11:03,320
The tape kept running.

262
00:11:03,700 --> 00:11:05,800
My father's voice said the third name again.

263
00:11:06,020 --> 00:11:07,520
Clear, without hesitation.

264
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:10,100
On a hotel floor that smelled of dust.

265
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:12,700
And of something that shouldn't have been kept for so long.

266
00:11:13,160 --> 00:11:15,160
Surai held the envelope with the typed label.

267
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:17,120
Everin didn't walk toward me.

268
00:11:17,420 --> 00:11:18,260
He stayed in the doorway.

269
00:11:18,900 --> 00:11:21,480
As if he knew that walking would be worse than staying still.

270
00:11:21,900 --> 00:11:23,380
I looked at him over the old machine.

271
00:11:23,860 --> 00:11:27,740
I looked at his surname written in my head in letters that suddenly carried another weight.

272
00:11:27,740 --> 00:11:31,140
For three months I'd forgotten what that surname was capable of doing.

273
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:33,300
The tape reminded me in four minutes.

274
00:11:39,020 --> 00:11:41,160
Penthouse had a view of the lake in good silence.

275
00:11:41,680 --> 00:11:44,720
It was the first time in three months that the silence bothered me.

276
00:11:44,920 --> 00:11:49,680
I arrived with the tape inside a large envelope, holding it with both hands as if it were heavier

277
00:11:49,680 --> 00:11:50,460
than it was.

278
00:11:50,880 --> 00:11:54,720
The paper was slightly crumpled at the edges from how much I'd gripped it in the car.

279
00:11:55,060 --> 00:11:57,740
Everin had come behind me with Dario in the other vehicle.

280
00:11:58,220 --> 00:11:59,820
He didn't try to talk to me in traffic.

281
00:12:00,320 --> 00:12:01,680
When I walked into the Penthouse,

282
00:12:01,680 --> 00:12:03,920
he was already sitting in the living room.

283
00:12:04,300 --> 00:12:06,660
Jacket opened and hands clasped in his lap,

284
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:09,800
waiting without hurry, without visible anxiety.

285
00:12:10,420 --> 00:12:11,560
He just pointed to the couch.

286
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:13,140
Do you want to listen again?

287
00:12:13,540 --> 00:12:14,500
I want you to listen.

288
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:19,680
I put the tape into the little tape player Dario had managed to find somewhere in the last two hours.

289
00:12:20,180 --> 00:12:22,700
The machine was old, a faded sand color,

290
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:26,620
with press buttons that made a satisfying mechanical click when they latched.

291
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:27,980
I pressed play.

292
00:12:28,260 --> 00:12:30,920
My father's voice came out again through that tiny speaker.

293
00:12:31,540 --> 00:12:36,240
Slightly muffled, as if it were coming from inside a room that had been closed for a long time.

294
00:12:37,420 --> 00:12:41,580
With that strange quality of something recorded carefully so it wouldn't be found.

295
00:12:42,920 --> 00:12:45,920
Everin listened without moving, without commenting,

296
00:12:46,760 --> 00:12:51,080
without crossing his arms or looking away or trying to protect me from what I already knew.

297
00:12:52,120 --> 00:12:53,660
When it ended, he stayed silent.

298
00:12:55,160 --> 00:12:57,860
The kind of silence that isn't an absence of an answer.

299
00:12:58,600 --> 00:12:59,480
It's an answer.

300
00:13:00,020 --> 00:13:00,500
Say something.

301
00:13:01,140 --> 00:13:03,340
Whatever you want me to say is going to sound like a defense.

302
00:13:03,880 --> 00:13:05,840
I'm not going to defend myself from this.

303
00:13:06,060 --> 00:13:07,400
He breathed in deep slowly.

304
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,040
I don't know this tape.

305
00:13:09,520 --> 00:13:10,140
It's your surname.

306
00:13:10,720 --> 00:13:11,120
I know.

307
00:13:11,580 --> 00:13:12,200
It's my father.

308
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:13,220
I know.

309
00:13:13,680 --> 00:13:14,500
So what do you know?

310
00:13:14,760 --> 00:13:15,900
He took a while to answer.

311
00:13:16,360 --> 00:13:21,040
He looked at the floor for a second and then looked at me with an expression I was still learning to read.

312
00:13:21,420 --> 00:13:22,340
It wasn't regret.

313
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:23,900
It wasn't an apology.

314
00:13:24,480 --> 00:13:26,160
It was something more honest than both.

315
00:13:26,160 --> 00:13:30,860
It was the face of a man who grew up without the luxury of pretending the world was simple.

316
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:33,920
That this happened before I existed as a melvani.

317
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:37,260
And that if you need space, I'll give it to you.

318
00:13:37,520 --> 00:13:38,620
I asked for space.

319
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:39,820
He gave it.

320
00:13:40,140 --> 00:13:41,300
Wednesday passed slowly.

321
00:13:41,880 --> 00:13:46,500
I slept in the guest room with the window a jar and the sound of the lake arriving in low waves

322
00:13:46,500 --> 00:13:47,700
that couldn't fill the room.

323
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:51,120
The mattress was too firm and smelled faintly of artificial lavender,

324
00:13:51,700 --> 00:13:53,660
that hotel scent that was supposed to be comforting.

325
00:13:54,220 --> 00:13:57,760
But that night only reminded me I was sleeping in a room that wasn't mine

326
00:13:57,760 --> 00:14:00,520
inside an apartment that still felt like his.

327
00:14:01,820 --> 00:14:04,040
I crossed paths with ever and twice in the hallway.

328
00:14:05,280 --> 00:14:09,000
One of those times his hair was wet and his shirt was open at the first button.

329
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:14,020
And both times he looked away with a politeness that hurt me more than if he'd insisted on talking.

330
00:14:15,040 --> 00:14:17,140
There was something in his care that weighed.

331
00:14:17,480 --> 00:14:20,600
As if keeping his distance were the greatest effort he'd ever made.

332
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:25,880
Thursday morning, Sarah showed up with coffee and a giant croissant wrapped in parchment paper.

333
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:27,060
Still warm.

334
00:14:27,540 --> 00:14:30,340
The heat of the bundle passed through my hands when she set it on the counter.

335
00:14:30,920 --> 00:14:32,660
And for a moment I just stared at it.

336
00:14:32,960 --> 00:14:35,400
As if the whole gesture were too complicated to receive.

337
00:14:35,900 --> 00:14:36,620
I brought carbs.

338
00:14:37,060 --> 00:14:38,140
I didn't bring good sense.

339
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:39,580
That's already a start.

340
00:14:40,020 --> 00:14:42,900
She sat on the kitchen counter and crossed her arms over the ledge.

341
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:46,400
With the posture of someone who was going to stay there as long as needed.

342
00:14:46,820 --> 00:14:48,760
She looked at the TV in the living room,

343
00:14:48,760 --> 00:14:50,420
which was on with no sound.

344
00:14:50,940 --> 00:14:52,900
I didn't even know why I'd turned it on.

345
00:14:53,280 --> 00:14:58,780
I'd turned it on because the silence of the penthouse became a concrete thing inside my chest if I let it grow.

346
00:15:00,780 --> 00:15:01,540
Look at the screen.

347
00:15:02,100 --> 00:15:02,540
I looked.

348
00:15:02,840 --> 00:15:04,980
It was the logo of the local gossip radio.

349
00:15:05,580 --> 00:15:07,980
The one I always pretended not to listen to.

350
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:13,040
But the two hosts playing studio in the background and a central microphone they used for everything.

351
00:15:13,520 --> 00:15:16,300
From neighborhood squabbles to national scandal.

352
00:15:16,300 --> 00:15:19,680
The headline underneath, in yellow capital letters,

353
00:15:20,100 --> 00:15:25,000
took up half the screen, criminal informants daughter organized the gala of the year.

354
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:27,860
So I pressed the remote and turned up the volume.

355
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:30,260
A piece of the tape played on the air.

356
00:15:30,580 --> 00:15:31,240
It was short.

357
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:32,680
Maybe 40 seconds.

358
00:15:33,220 --> 00:15:35,880
It was exactly the part where my father gave the second name.

359
00:15:36,260 --> 00:15:37,220
There was no context.

360
00:15:37,780 --> 00:15:39,300
There was no story before it.

361
00:15:39,580 --> 00:15:42,100
There was none of the part where his voice grew more tense.

362
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:44,640
As if he were choosing his words very carefully.

363
00:15:44,640 --> 00:15:47,000
As if the situation weren't simple.

364
00:15:48,040 --> 00:15:48,700
There was nothing.

365
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:51,940
It was just his voice saying a man's name.

366
00:15:52,520 --> 00:15:54,140
Clean and alone on the air.

367
00:15:54,640 --> 00:15:57,760
Dry as an accusation that already arrived with the verdict ready.

368
00:15:59,040 --> 00:15:59,200
How?

369
00:16:00,020 --> 00:16:00,540
I asked.

370
00:16:00,900 --> 00:16:02,280
So I didn't answer right away.

371
00:16:02,720 --> 00:16:04,460
There was a slight tightening in her jaw.

372
00:16:04,940 --> 00:16:06,680
The sign I knew for contained anger.

373
00:16:07,180 --> 00:16:07,940
I don't know.

374
00:16:08,160 --> 00:16:09,280
But I'm going to find out.

375
00:16:09,580 --> 00:16:11,360
I got up and walked to the living room window.

376
00:16:11,360 --> 00:16:12,920
The lake was calm.

377
00:16:13,340 --> 00:16:15,220
A cold gray blue autumn morning.

378
00:16:15,740 --> 00:16:18,140
With a few small boats too far off to identify.

379
00:16:18,740 --> 00:16:22,200
And a thin mist near the shore that made everything slightly imprecise.

380
00:16:22,640 --> 00:16:24,480
Like a photo taken with the wrong lens.

381
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:29,180
I thought about how many people were listening to that sentence from my father at that exact moment.

382
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:30,160
In cars.

383
00:16:30,580 --> 00:16:31,520
In the coffee line.

384
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:33,420
In the dentist's waiting room.

385
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:34,700
In the office elevator.

386
00:16:35,340 --> 00:16:38,840
I thought about the hotel sponsors hearing it on the way to the 10 o'clock meeting.

387
00:16:38,840 --> 00:16:41,560
I thought about the parents of my school classmates.

388
00:16:42,220 --> 00:16:44,600
People who had known my father at neighborhood dinners.

389
00:16:45,120 --> 00:16:48,620
People who would swear now that they'd always suspected something about him.

390
00:16:48,740 --> 00:16:50,120
They cut everything that mattered.

391
00:16:50,820 --> 00:16:51,100
I said.

392
00:16:51,580 --> 00:16:53,080
Those creeps live off this.

393
00:16:53,440 --> 00:16:54,400
It's diaper journalism.

394
00:16:55,160 --> 00:16:55,680
Dirty it.

395
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:56,380
Throw it out.

396
00:16:56,660 --> 00:16:57,660
Dirty another one.

397
00:16:57,960 --> 00:16:58,480
I laughed.

398
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,600
It was a dry, short laugh.

399
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:03,260
The kind that comes before crying if I'm not careful.

400
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:06,140
So I came to me and squeezed my hand over the counter.

401
00:17:06,640 --> 00:17:08,240
You need to get out of here for a while.

402
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:09,100
I left.

403
00:17:09,660 --> 00:17:10,800
I went to the old apartment.

404
00:17:11,420 --> 00:17:13,300
The apartment where I'd lived before the gala.

405
00:17:13,820 --> 00:17:16,280
Where I'd made the dumbest decision of my adult life.

406
00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:19,580
Eiring an escort because I was afraid of being looked at with pity.

407
00:17:20,040 --> 00:17:21,660
The apartment was still in my name.

408
00:17:22,080 --> 00:17:23,940
I hadn't been able to hand back the key.

409
00:17:24,340 --> 00:17:26,280
There was something superstitious in it.

410
00:17:26,560 --> 00:17:30,120
In keeping a piece of myself stored in a place where no one could reach me.

411
00:17:30,340 --> 00:17:31,220
I opened the door.

412
00:17:31,640 --> 00:17:33,180
The smell of stale air.

413
00:17:33,560 --> 00:17:35,740
And of an old perfume I no longer wore.

414
00:17:35,740 --> 00:17:38,300
Baintly sweet and a little suffocating.

415
00:17:38,840 --> 00:17:42,900
With that added layer of dust places gather when they go a long time without breathing.

416
00:17:43,360 --> 00:17:45,200
The furniture was covered with white sheets.

417
00:17:45,660 --> 00:17:48,820
And the light coming through the shutters created stripes on the wood floor.

418
00:17:49,280 --> 00:17:50,980
I walked straight to the hallway closet.

419
00:17:51,460 --> 00:17:52,440
Open the bottom drawer.

420
00:17:52,940 --> 00:17:54,680
And took out my father's box of photos.

421
00:17:55,260 --> 00:17:56,240
I sat on the floor.

422
00:17:56,720 --> 00:18:00,240
There were birthday photos and vacation photos and Sunday morning photos.

423
00:18:00,740 --> 00:18:03,060
There was a photo of him carrying me in his arms.

424
00:18:03,060 --> 00:18:04,220
On the beach.

425
00:18:04,700 --> 00:18:06,540
With a floppy straw hat on his head.

426
00:18:06,860 --> 00:18:08,960
And his eyes half closed from all the sun.

427
00:18:09,320 --> 00:18:12,400
There was the yellow dress he'd bought me in some small town market.

428
00:18:12,780 --> 00:18:15,820
Holded at the bottom of the box because I'd never been able to throw it away.

429
00:18:16,320 --> 00:18:17,740
The fabric was slightly faded.

430
00:18:18,180 --> 00:18:21,620
With a permanent crease down the center where it had been rolled up for years.

431
00:18:21,940 --> 00:18:27,040
And as I ran my fingers across the surface I thought that faded yellow was the most his thing I still had.

432
00:18:27,480 --> 00:18:30,540
And underneath the dress, I found the birthday cassette tape.

433
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:32,140
I remembered right away.

434
00:18:32,140 --> 00:18:35,080
He'd recorded an entire tape from my 12th birthday.

435
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:36,300
He'd sung.

436
00:18:36,740 --> 00:18:37,780
Read a piece of a book.

437
00:18:38,260 --> 00:18:43,600
Sent a message to my future self with that ceremonial seriousness he put into things he considered important.

438
00:18:44,180 --> 00:18:47,240
I hadn't listened to the tape a single time in over 20 years.

439
00:18:47,620 --> 00:18:50,420
I was afraid his voice would come out different from what I remembered.

440
00:18:51,060 --> 00:18:52,120
Thenner, stranger,

441
00:18:52,920 --> 00:18:54,520
Deformed by time or by memory.

442
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:56,960
There was a portable tape player in the box.

443
00:18:57,520 --> 00:18:59,040
Smaller than the palm of my hand.

444
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:00,640
The battery still worked.

445
00:19:00,640 --> 00:19:04,220
I slotted the tape in carefully as if the plastic were fragile.

446
00:19:04,700 --> 00:19:07,360
As if the wrong pressure could erase what was stored inside.

447
00:19:07,860 --> 00:19:08,660
I pressed the button.

448
00:19:09,160 --> 00:19:10,960
His voice came out singing happy birthday.

449
00:19:11,540 --> 00:19:12,700
It was the same voice.

450
00:19:13,280 --> 00:19:14,140
The same texture.

451
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:15,900
The same slight rasp.

452
00:19:16,320 --> 00:19:21,040
The same way of holding the A at the end of words as if each syllable needed more room than usual.

453
00:19:21,460 --> 00:19:23,120
It was the voice from the vault tape.

454
00:19:23,540 --> 00:19:26,260
It was the voice of every Sunday morning of my childhood.

455
00:19:26,840 --> 00:19:29,760
Of the breakfast table with the big cup that was always his.

456
00:19:29,760 --> 00:19:34,900
Of the dark hallway when he checked whether I was asleep before turning off the living room light.

457
00:19:35,380 --> 00:19:36,320
I started to cry.

458
00:19:36,780 --> 00:19:38,520
The way I hadn't cried since the altar.

459
00:19:39,040 --> 00:19:39,620
No sound.

460
00:19:40,100 --> 00:19:40,740
No performance.

461
00:19:41,380 --> 00:19:44,500
My hand flat on my chest as if I needed to hold something in.

462
00:19:44,660 --> 00:19:46,460
I sat on the floor of the empty apartment.

463
00:19:47,080 --> 00:19:48,960
With the stripes of light across my back.

464
00:19:49,280 --> 00:19:51,220
The smell of stale air all around.

465
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:54,960
Listening to my father sing happy birthday to me at 12 years old.

466
00:19:55,360 --> 00:19:59,560
And I kept thinking about the moment he'd had to choose between protecting me and continuing to

467
00:19:59,560 --> 00:20:01,440
look like a simple man in my eyes.

468
00:20:01,780 --> 00:20:02,780
Whether he'd hesitated.

469
00:20:03,340 --> 00:20:04,960
Whether it had been easy or impossible.

470
00:20:05,740 --> 00:20:07,640
Whether he knew in that birthday recording.

471
00:20:08,240 --> 00:20:09,360
What he'd already done.

472
00:20:09,820 --> 00:20:11,620
Sarai came to get me in the late afternoon.

473
00:20:12,220 --> 00:20:13,360
She didn't ask anything.

474
00:20:13,860 --> 00:20:16,180
Which was the most generous gesture she could have offered.

475
00:20:16,680 --> 00:20:17,980
I went back to the penthouse.

476
00:20:18,480 --> 00:20:19,720
The lake was already dark.

477
00:20:20,100 --> 00:20:25,260
The boat lights reflecting on the water and crooked trembling lines that dissolved as soon as the wind passed.

478
00:20:25,680 --> 00:20:26,500
I went in.

479
00:20:26,900 --> 00:20:27,880
Everin was in the kitchen.

480
00:20:28,380 --> 00:20:30,040
Sleeve still rolled to his elbow.

481
00:20:30,640 --> 00:20:34,080
Making something in a pan that he turned off when he heard me arrive.

482
00:20:34,560 --> 00:20:35,320
A quiet movement.

483
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:36,440
Unhurried.

484
00:20:36,980 --> 00:20:39,840
As if he'd been waiting for this hour without admitting he was waiting.

485
00:20:40,340 --> 00:20:44,000
He looked at me with the kind of look that asks for nothing and promises nothing.

486
00:20:44,600 --> 00:20:45,400
It just receives.

487
00:20:46,120 --> 00:20:48,280
I'm going to sleep in the guest room one more night.

488
00:20:48,760 --> 00:20:49,320
That's fine.

489
00:20:49,860 --> 00:20:51,000
It's not because of you.

490
00:20:51,460 --> 00:20:52,020
I know.

491
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:53,420
I walked down the hallway.

492
00:20:53,980 --> 00:20:54,900
I stopped halfway.

493
00:20:54,900 --> 00:20:57,560
The wood floor was cold under my socks.

494
00:20:57,960 --> 00:21:02,880
And the hallway had that late night dimness that made everything a little more honest than during the day.

495
00:21:03,100 --> 00:21:04,020
I went back.

496
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:04,740
Everin.

497
00:21:05,920 --> 00:21:07,540
Thank you for not trying to fix it.

498
00:21:07,740 --> 00:21:09,140
He lowered his eyes for a moment.

499
00:21:09,580 --> 00:21:12,500
When he looked at me again, there was something different there.

500
00:21:12,760 --> 00:21:17,440
Not hurt, not resignation, but a kind of calm, the cost dearly.

501
00:21:17,800 --> 00:21:20,460
The kind of calm he must have learned the worst way possible.

502
00:21:20,840 --> 00:21:22,280
I don't know how to fix this.

503
00:21:22,560 --> 00:21:22,980
I know.

504
00:21:23,480 --> 00:21:24,020
That's why.

505
00:21:24,020 --> 00:21:29,720
That night, before lying down, I went through the hotel lobby to pick up a folder I'd left in the office.

506
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:31,360
The reception was quiet.

507
00:21:31,880 --> 00:21:36,580
Only one clerk at the desk and the reduced late night lighting that made the marble floor warmer than

508
00:21:36,580 --> 00:21:37,340
during the day.

509
00:21:37,720 --> 00:21:40,040
The neighborhood paper was folded on top of the counter.

510
00:21:40,560 --> 00:21:41,340
A small headline.

511
00:21:41,860 --> 00:21:43,460
In the lower corner of the front page.

512
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:45,540
Calvin Harth was going to trial.

513
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:47,140
I looked for two seconds.

514
00:21:47,660 --> 00:21:48,600
I didn't feel anger.

515
00:21:49,160 --> 00:21:50,140
I didn't feel relief.

516
00:21:50,660 --> 00:21:52,040
I didn't feel anything concrete.

517
00:21:52,040 --> 00:21:55,840
Which was strange after so many months waiting for exactly that headline.

518
00:21:56,440 --> 00:22:00,000
It was as if it had turned small inside me without my noticing when.

519
00:22:01,260 --> 00:22:03,340
I put the paper back in its place and left.

520
00:22:04,360 --> 00:22:06,220
I got back to the penthouse close to 11.

521
00:22:07,220 --> 00:22:11,280
Ever and had already laying down, or had the delicacy to pretend he had.

522
00:22:12,140 --> 00:22:13,660
I took off my shoes in the hallway.

523
00:22:14,300 --> 00:22:14,580
Slowly.

524
00:22:15,240 --> 00:22:16,240
So I wouldn't make noise.

525
00:22:16,740 --> 00:22:17,920
I went to the guest room.

526
00:22:18,240 --> 00:22:19,860
I laid down with the window a jar.

527
00:22:19,860 --> 00:22:23,960
The cold off the late coming in and thin waves that barely moved the curtain.

528
00:22:24,440 --> 00:22:25,280
The doorbell rang.

529
00:22:25,780 --> 00:22:27,380
I looked at the clock on the nightstand.

530
00:22:27,980 --> 00:22:29,020
11.04.

531
00:22:29,440 --> 00:22:31,400
No one showed up at that penthouse unannounced.

532
00:22:31,920 --> 00:22:34,820
Dario filtered everything, including late night visitors.

533
00:22:35,500 --> 00:22:38,220
Unless it was someone Dario couldn't filter for another reason.

534
00:22:38,700 --> 00:22:39,620
I got up.

535
00:22:39,860 --> 00:22:41,820
I walked to the entrance monitor in the hallway.

536
00:22:42,300 --> 00:22:45,000
There was a woman standing downstairs in the camera's frame.

537
00:22:45,500 --> 00:22:47,420
Dark heavy coat, straight shoulders.

538
00:22:47,420 --> 00:22:51,140
Grey hair pulled into a low bun with a firmness that seemed deliberate.

539
00:22:51,680 --> 00:22:53,720
She wasn't looking at the inner com or the camera.

540
00:22:54,300 --> 00:22:58,480
She was looking straight ahead with the specific patience of someone who knows she's going to be

541
00:22:58,480 --> 00:22:59,020
let in.

542
00:22:59,840 --> 00:23:04,380
When she lifted her eyes to the monitor, I recognized her without ever having seen her before.

543
00:23:04,760 --> 00:23:08,840
They were black firm eyes that I knew from every morning of the last three months on someone

544
00:23:08,840 --> 00:23:09,660
else's face.

545
00:23:10,060 --> 00:23:11,940
I pressed the inner com with a trembling hand.

546
00:23:12,500 --> 00:23:12,780
Yes?

547
00:23:13,280 --> 00:23:15,540
Her voice came weighted with a light Italian accent.

548
00:23:16,220 --> 00:23:18,120
Precise without affectation.

549
00:23:18,520 --> 00:23:19,080
Miss Cross.

550
00:23:19,700 --> 00:23:20,520
I am Bruno Melvani.

551
00:23:21,040 --> 00:23:24,440
I need to tell you something about your father before my son finds out on his own.

552
00:23:29,860 --> 00:23:34,620
Doorbell buzzed again, and the sound pushed me toward the door before I decided to open it.

553
00:23:34,840 --> 00:23:36,220
Everyone was already in the hallway.

554
00:23:36,880 --> 00:23:37,360
Barefoot.

555
00:23:37,640 --> 00:23:39,820
Black shirt wrinkled like a man who hadn't slept.

556
00:23:40,460 --> 00:23:42,020
His eyes met mine for a second.

557
00:23:42,460 --> 00:23:43,340
A long second.

558
00:23:43,760 --> 00:23:46,040
Waded with a question neither of us put into words.

559
00:23:46,560 --> 00:23:47,840
He didn't ask who it was.

560
00:23:48,380 --> 00:23:49,400
Maybe he already knew.

561
00:23:49,400 --> 00:23:54,260
I opened the penthouse door, and the woman waiting on the other side took off her coat with

562
00:23:54,260 --> 00:23:58,400
the delicacy of someone entering a home for the first time without being sure she'd be welcome.

563
00:23:58,960 --> 00:23:59,860
60 something.

564
00:24:00,360 --> 00:24:02,000
Gray hair pulled into a low bun.

565
00:24:02,520 --> 00:24:04,340
Discrete lipstick invaded wine.

566
00:24:04,740 --> 00:24:07,600
A thin chain of old gold resting on the skin of her chest.

567
00:24:07,960 --> 00:24:10,080
The Italian accent appeared in the first word.

568
00:24:10,640 --> 00:24:13,140
Light like the smoke still rising from the kitchen coffee.

569
00:24:13,660 --> 00:24:15,140
The one I'd forgotten to turn off.

570
00:24:15,480 --> 00:24:16,480
May I come in, Noelia?

571
00:24:17,060 --> 00:24:17,980
She knew my name.

572
00:24:17,980 --> 00:24:22,340
She knew enough to wait until 11 at night at the entrance of a building that wasn't hers.

573
00:24:22,760 --> 00:24:26,500
With late cold outside and a discretion that told me more than any introduction.

574
00:24:27,160 --> 00:24:27,640
You may.

575
00:24:28,080 --> 00:24:28,540
My answered.

576
00:24:29,180 --> 00:24:30,100
And step to side.

577
00:24:30,660 --> 00:24:32,540
Ever and approach to his mother from the inside.

578
00:24:33,100 --> 00:24:34,080
Without touching her.

579
00:24:34,420 --> 00:24:36,780
The two exchanged a short, dry look.

580
00:24:37,200 --> 00:24:39,280
And I realized that between them too.

581
00:24:39,600 --> 00:24:40,800
There were old silences.

582
00:24:41,340 --> 00:24:44,040
The kind carried for decades without needing words.

583
00:24:44,580 --> 00:24:46,700
Because the words wouldn't ease anything anyway.

584
00:24:46,700 --> 00:24:49,920
Bruno Melvani set her purse on the coffee table carefully.

585
00:24:50,560 --> 00:24:51,720
As if the gesture mattered.

586
00:24:52,280 --> 00:24:54,760
And looked at me with a calm that hurt more than any hurry.

587
00:24:55,220 --> 00:24:57,340
I came before he found out on his own.

588
00:24:57,580 --> 00:24:58,300
She said.

589
00:24:58,640 --> 00:25:00,120
Tilting her head toward her son.

590
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:04,560
There are things about your father that I had to keep for more than 20 years.

591
00:25:04,840 --> 00:25:08,220
And that are now coming out of a vault I believed no longer existed.

592
00:25:09,360 --> 00:25:10,720
I felt my stomach tightened.

593
00:25:11,940 --> 00:25:13,160
Bruno sat on the couch.

594
00:25:13,160 --> 00:25:15,640
Smooth her dark skirt over her knees.

595
00:25:16,360 --> 00:25:17,640
And waited for me to sit too.

596
00:25:18,820 --> 00:25:21,720
The apartment was quiet except for the low wind at the windows.

597
00:25:22,740 --> 00:25:23,920
Ever in stayed standing.

598
00:25:24,620 --> 00:25:25,980
Leaning against the kitchen counter.

599
00:25:26,680 --> 00:25:27,820
Two steps behind us.

600
00:25:28,940 --> 00:25:29,800
He didn't interrupt.

601
00:25:30,960 --> 00:25:32,660
In that house, that night.

602
00:25:33,200 --> 00:25:34,480
The voice belonged to his mother.

603
00:25:35,020 --> 00:25:37,840
And Taro Cross came to my husband 22 years ago.

604
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:39,300
Bruno began slowly.

605
00:25:39,800 --> 00:25:42,120
Choosing each word like someone crossing thin ice.

606
00:25:42,120 --> 00:25:44,120
Not to sell anyone out.

607
00:25:44,340 --> 00:25:45,100
To infiltrate.

608
00:25:45,580 --> 00:25:49,400
There was a dissident faction that had started threatening entire families by name.

609
00:25:49,860 --> 00:25:53,900
Your mother and you were on a list that reached your father's hands from inside a department he

610
00:25:53,900 --> 00:25:54,180
coordinated.

611
00:25:54,780 --> 00:25:55,760
He had two choices.

612
00:25:56,340 --> 00:26:00,100
Get you out of the country and lose you another way or agree to go in.

613
00:26:00,480 --> 00:26:03,320
The coffee cup on the coffee table stopped existing for me.

614
00:26:03,620 --> 00:26:07,560
I heard Bruno's breathing louder than any sound coming from the building or the street.

615
00:26:07,960 --> 00:26:08,600
He agreed.

616
00:26:09,220 --> 00:26:09,900
She went on.

617
00:26:09,900 --> 00:26:12,600
He arranged a staged handover with the old Melvani.

618
00:26:13,240 --> 00:26:16,320
And Taro would give three names that were already technically dead.

619
00:26:16,660 --> 00:26:18,560
From the standpoint of the family's accounting.

620
00:26:19,220 --> 00:26:22,040
And in exchange the dissidents would believe he was with them.

621
00:26:22,280 --> 00:26:23,400
It was a long game.

622
00:26:23,800 --> 00:26:25,920
The plan was to expose everything in the end.

623
00:26:26,300 --> 00:26:27,960
With names and dates and faces.

624
00:26:28,640 --> 00:26:29,980
The old Melvani knew.

625
00:26:30,300 --> 00:26:30,860
I knew.

626
00:26:31,260 --> 00:26:35,060
For years, it was the most expensive secret of my marriage.

627
00:26:35,540 --> 00:26:36,780
The three men who died.

628
00:26:37,280 --> 00:26:39,000
My voice came out almost breathless.

629
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:43,240
They died because someone from inside our family sold the plan ahead of time.

630
00:26:43,560 --> 00:26:45,920
It wasn't your father's tape that killed those men.

631
00:26:46,320 --> 00:26:47,640
It was internal betrayal.

632
00:26:48,360 --> 00:26:50,280
On Taro found out who had sold them out.

633
00:26:50,620 --> 00:26:52,680
He was going to expose it in both directions.

634
00:26:53,320 --> 00:26:54,820
To the dissidents to the police.

635
00:26:55,260 --> 00:26:56,860
He was killed before he could.

636
00:26:57,260 --> 00:26:58,280
I lifted my eyes.

637
00:26:58,700 --> 00:26:59,160
She waited.

638
00:26:59,680 --> 00:27:01,580
I needed to hear the name from her mouth.

639
00:27:02,020 --> 00:27:02,920
And she knew it.

640
00:27:03,200 --> 00:27:06,540
New it the same way you know when someone is holding a door from the inside.

641
00:27:06,540 --> 00:27:09,140
Waiting for someone on the other side to push.

642
00:27:09,860 --> 00:27:10,640
Massimo Grell.

643
00:27:11,040 --> 00:27:11,580
Bruno said.

644
00:27:12,080 --> 00:27:13,700
It was Massimo who killed your father.

645
00:27:14,180 --> 00:27:16,460
And my husband died in the ambush that followed.

646
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:19,780
Precisely because Massimo passed our movements to the dissidents.

647
00:27:20,320 --> 00:27:23,940
In one week, he had the two widows he needed to control what was left.

648
00:27:24,540 --> 00:27:25,200
Behind me.

649
00:27:25,460 --> 00:27:28,120
I heard the sound of ever in breathing slowly through his nose.

650
00:27:28,620 --> 00:27:31,180
Like someone holding an entire wave inside his chest.

651
00:27:31,580 --> 00:27:33,220
So as not to knock the room down.

652
00:27:33,620 --> 00:27:34,900
Why did you never tell?

653
00:27:34,900 --> 00:27:35,720
I asked.

654
00:27:36,220 --> 00:27:39,960
Because as long as Massimo thought I didn't know, he kept me alive.

655
00:27:40,440 --> 00:27:41,020
Bruno answered.

656
00:27:41,580 --> 00:27:42,920
Without looking away from me.

657
00:27:43,200 --> 00:27:47,460
And as long as Everin believed in the father figure Massimo built over two decades.

658
00:27:48,220 --> 00:27:50,360
Massimo wouldn't need to kill my son too.

659
00:27:50,620 --> 00:27:51,460
I looked at Everin.

660
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:52,540
He was still.

661
00:27:53,140 --> 00:27:54,800
Hand closed over the stone counter.

662
00:27:55,340 --> 00:27:57,300
His knuckles white against the dark granite.

663
00:27:57,720 --> 00:27:58,440
He said nothing.

664
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:00,320
He only tilted his head.

665
00:28:00,720 --> 00:28:00,900
Slowly.

666
00:28:01,560 --> 00:28:04,880
Like someone recognizing a pain that had already been inside him for a long time.

667
00:28:05,660 --> 00:28:09,040
Waiting to be named by someone who survived to name it.

668
00:28:09,260 --> 00:28:10,180
Bruno stood up.

669
00:28:10,500 --> 00:28:14,020
She ran her hand across my face with a lightness that didn't ask permission.

670
00:28:14,540 --> 00:28:15,420
And even so.

671
00:28:15,700 --> 00:28:16,740
Didn't invade anything.

672
00:28:17,280 --> 00:28:21,600
It was the gesture of a woman who had learned the difference between consoling and invading.

673
00:28:22,160 --> 00:28:23,980
Your father died protecting you, Noelia.

674
00:28:24,660 --> 00:28:26,320
The old vault held the wrong tape.

675
00:28:26,880 --> 00:28:28,800
Somewhere, there's a complete tape.

676
00:28:29,220 --> 00:28:31,160
The one where he explains everything in detail.

677
00:28:31,520 --> 00:28:34,180
With the plan, the names, and the intentions.

678
00:28:34,740 --> 00:28:36,780
Massimo spent 22 years looking.

679
00:28:37,280 --> 00:28:39,780
If he learns that the tape from the envelope reached the hotel,

680
00:28:40,260 --> 00:28:41,340
he'll come after the rest.

681
00:28:41,720 --> 00:28:43,000
And he'll come after me first.

682
00:28:43,480 --> 00:28:45,500
She picked up the purse from the center of the table.

683
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:48,320
Everin finally moved to walk her to the door.

684
00:28:48,720 --> 00:28:51,980
His mother placed an open hand on her son's chest for two seconds.

685
00:28:52,540 --> 00:28:53,420
Just two.

686
00:28:53,660 --> 00:28:56,360
Like someone touching a wall to feel whether it's still standing.

687
00:28:57,000 --> 00:28:58,560
Whether the material still holds.

688
00:28:59,080 --> 00:29:00,400
I'm not going home tonight.

689
00:29:00,840 --> 00:29:01,820
She said to him.

690
00:29:01,820 --> 00:29:04,060
Her voice low and firm without drama.

691
00:29:04,640 --> 00:29:06,160
I'll get a room far from here.

692
00:29:06,440 --> 00:29:07,660
No one needs to know where.

693
00:29:08,100 --> 00:29:09,400
The door closed behind her.

694
00:29:09,720 --> 00:29:12,280
The sound of the latch was the only noise in the whole apartment.

695
00:29:12,840 --> 00:29:14,240
I stayed sitting on the couch.

696
00:29:14,740 --> 00:29:16,220
Even in state in the same place,

697
00:29:16,540 --> 00:29:18,540
leaning against the counter without turning around.

698
00:29:19,380 --> 00:29:21,020
I went to the kitchen when she left.

699
00:29:21,380 --> 00:29:22,300
It wasn't fleeing.

700
00:29:22,860 --> 00:29:26,960
It was the only wall in the house where I could stay standing without looking at Noelia.

701
00:29:27,560 --> 00:29:30,400
While my world finished falling in orderly silence.

702
00:29:30,400 --> 00:29:32,200
Peace by peace.

703
00:29:32,580 --> 00:29:35,060
Like a structure collapsing from the inside out.

704
00:29:35,460 --> 00:29:37,600
I turned on the faucet just for the sound.

705
00:29:38,060 --> 00:29:42,400
I braised both hands on the cold stone counter and closed my eyes.

706
00:29:42,840 --> 00:29:45,220
The first thing that came wasn't Massimo.

707
00:29:45,720 --> 00:29:46,620
It was her.

708
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:48,220
Backstage at the hotel.

709
00:29:48,720 --> 00:29:49,600
Three months ago.

710
00:29:49,960 --> 00:29:53,520
The hallway smelled of expensive flowers and a electrical cable

711
00:29:53,520 --> 00:29:56,700
heated by the spotlights to set up crew head left on.

712
00:29:56,920 --> 00:29:59,340
I'd come in through the service door as arranged.

713
00:29:59,340 --> 00:30:02,040
The false name on the tip of my tongue.

714
00:30:02,620 --> 00:30:04,940
The crest ring in the inner pocket of my jacket.

715
00:30:05,560 --> 00:30:08,400
Away from my right hand for the first time in years.

716
00:30:08,720 --> 00:30:12,520
She appeared at the end of the hallway with a clipboard pressed against her chest.

717
00:30:12,920 --> 00:30:14,720
And a wet charcoal colored dress.

718
00:30:14,860 --> 00:30:16,520
Her hair still damp from rain.

719
00:30:16,860 --> 00:30:20,400
Her mouth tense like someone who'd spent hours holding in a speech.

720
00:30:20,900 --> 00:30:23,460
She looked at me as if she were checking a catering order.

721
00:30:23,940 --> 00:30:27,360
I scanned the three exits before I noticed the way she breathed.

722
00:30:27,360 --> 00:30:29,500
Scanning exits was muscle memory.

723
00:30:29,900 --> 00:30:34,700
Noticing the way she breathed was the first thing I'd done without deciding to in a long time.

724
00:30:35,060 --> 00:30:36,360
I remembered the ballroom.

725
00:30:36,840 --> 00:30:42,060
The moment the exfiance approached with a rehearsed line and she answered with sarcasm.

726
00:30:42,400 --> 00:30:44,120
Before I even had to open my mouth.

727
00:30:44,620 --> 00:30:45,320
It was there.

728
00:30:45,640 --> 00:30:49,940
It was exactly there that something happened that I didn't have a name for in my vocabulary.

729
00:30:50,820 --> 00:30:53,220
I'd walked into that gala to identify a traitor.

730
00:30:53,800 --> 00:30:56,720
And in four seconds a woman I'd never seen in my life.

731
00:30:56,720 --> 00:31:01,860
Had parried a public humiliation with the serenity of someone who had nothing left to lose.

732
00:31:02,320 --> 00:31:04,900
And still chose to defend herself with elegance.

733
00:31:05,420 --> 00:31:07,020
I knew how to identify courage.

734
00:31:07,540 --> 00:31:09,540
It had been my trade since I was 22.

735
00:31:10,200 --> 00:31:11,420
This was something else.

736
00:31:11,700 --> 00:31:14,460
This was a woman who laughed when she was about to cry.

737
00:31:14,960 --> 00:31:19,240
And I recognized the texture of that laugh before I even knew her full name.

738
00:31:19,680 --> 00:31:23,380
The service hallway came next, out of chronological order.

739
00:31:23,920 --> 00:31:24,960
The side door.

740
00:31:24,960 --> 00:31:30,180
The smell of flowers and of invisible work mixing in the air between the white walls.

741
00:31:30,660 --> 00:31:32,580
She said she didn't know who I was.

742
00:31:33,040 --> 00:31:37,220
I answered that she was the first person in a long time I didn't want to manipulate.

743
00:31:37,980 --> 00:31:38,760
It was true.

744
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:42,260
I hadn't predicted it would be true when I opened my mouth.

745
00:31:42,780 --> 00:31:46,600
Because the truth wasn't usually my starting point in any conversation.

746
00:31:47,240 --> 00:31:50,940
My fingers moved toward her face a millimeter before her chin rose.

747
00:31:51,380 --> 00:31:52,000
I stopped.

748
00:31:52,540 --> 00:31:53,220
She stopped.

749
00:31:53,220 --> 00:31:56,780
It was the first time in my life I stopped out of respect.

750
00:31:57,200 --> 00:31:57,920
Not calculation.

751
00:31:58,680 --> 00:31:59,760
And then the big screen.

752
00:32:00,320 --> 00:32:02,400
My face on national broadcast.

753
00:32:03,060 --> 00:32:04,920
The ballroom that froze in a second.

754
00:32:05,440 --> 00:32:07,780
The rivals coming in through the side doors.

755
00:32:08,240 --> 00:32:09,620
I could have left through the back.

756
00:32:10,040 --> 00:32:11,920
I'd had two roots mapped since arriving.

757
00:32:12,240 --> 00:32:13,180
It was the rule.

758
00:32:13,420 --> 00:32:14,680
It was always the rule.

759
00:32:15,100 --> 00:32:19,620
The first instruction of any family head was to preserve your own head above all else.

760
00:32:20,060 --> 00:32:21,720
I looked at her across the ballroom.

761
00:32:21,720 --> 00:32:24,720
She looked back at me with disgust, with fear,

762
00:32:25,220 --> 00:32:28,440
with the remnant of an anger that hadn't yet crashed down on me.

763
00:32:28,620 --> 00:32:29,460
And she stayed.

764
00:32:29,940 --> 00:32:30,860
She didn't run.

765
00:32:31,220 --> 00:32:35,360
She stayed with her feet planted on the marble of the ballroom she herself had organized.

766
00:32:35,960 --> 00:32:37,680
I stayed because she had stayed.

767
00:32:38,080 --> 00:32:43,220
It was the first time in my life I understood why my father used to say that silence was power.

768
00:32:43,700 --> 00:32:49,260
And that power was the only thing worth less than standing beside the person you choose to stand with.

769
00:32:49,260 --> 00:32:51,320
I opened my eyes over the sink.

770
00:32:51,740 --> 00:32:53,080
The water was still running.

771
00:32:53,580 --> 00:32:54,280
Cold now.

772
00:32:54,600 --> 00:32:56,880
And that was when the other memory came back.

773
00:32:57,360 --> 00:32:59,320
The one from the morning after the gala.

774
00:32:59,800 --> 00:33:01,960
The car pulling out of the hotel's basement.

775
00:33:02,500 --> 00:33:03,500
The engine low.

776
00:33:04,240 --> 00:33:05,760
Chicago's streets still wet.

777
00:33:06,180 --> 00:33:07,320
Massimo in the back seat.

778
00:33:07,760 --> 00:33:08,160
Paternal.

779
00:33:08,740 --> 00:33:09,860
His shoulders relaxed.

780
00:33:10,420 --> 00:33:14,500
Smiling with that tenderness of someone who had raised me after my father's death.

781
00:33:14,760 --> 00:33:15,700
He said in Italian,

782
00:33:15,700 --> 00:33:17,420
You deserve it, son.

783
00:33:17,880 --> 00:33:20,880
With the calm of someone who believes every word he chooses.

784
00:33:21,480 --> 00:33:22,920
I smiled back that day.

785
00:33:23,360 --> 00:33:24,480
I squeezed his shoulder.

786
00:33:25,120 --> 00:33:26,380
I thought it was pride.

787
00:33:27,460 --> 00:33:28,500
22 years.

788
00:33:29,060 --> 00:33:33,440
Massimo had been at my side in every important decision I'd made as head of the family.

789
00:33:33,980 --> 00:33:37,860
Including the one that led me to pretend to be an escort to identify a traitor,

790
00:33:38,100 --> 00:33:39,660
laundering money through the event.

791
00:33:40,020 --> 00:33:43,860
The one who had convinced me, with soft words and a father's patience,

792
00:33:43,860 --> 00:33:47,800
that the traitor was inside the hotel and not inside my own office.

793
00:33:48,340 --> 00:33:49,240
Had been Massimo.

794
00:33:49,700 --> 00:33:51,100
I shut off the faucet.

795
00:33:51,400 --> 00:33:54,520
The sentence in the car weighed three times as much now.

796
00:33:54,880 --> 00:33:55,920
You deserve it, son.

797
00:33:56,380 --> 00:34:00,680
He said, deserve, because he knew exactly what I didn't deserve to know.

798
00:34:00,840 --> 00:34:01,780
He said, son.

799
00:34:02,300 --> 00:34:07,140
Because 22 years earlier, he'd killed the man who was trying to give two women back their own names.

800
00:34:07,520 --> 00:34:08,700
I breathed in deep.

801
00:34:09,220 --> 00:34:09,540
Once.

802
00:34:10,140 --> 00:34:10,540
Slow.

803
00:34:11,140 --> 00:34:11,980
Through my nose.

804
00:34:11,980 --> 00:34:15,540
It was all I could allow myself without breaking something.

805
00:34:15,900 --> 00:34:19,360
When Evern came back from the kitchen, he didn't try to touch me.

806
00:34:19,580 --> 00:34:24,380
He sat at the other end of the couch, with a meter of space between us that neither of us had the

807
00:34:24,380 --> 00:34:28,360
energy to cross, and stayed looking at the floor with his elbows on his knees.

808
00:34:28,800 --> 00:34:29,660
I need a day.

809
00:34:30,020 --> 00:34:31,880
I said, before he tried anything.

810
00:34:32,440 --> 00:34:33,900
He nodded without lifting his head.

811
00:34:34,260 --> 00:34:35,280
Not to leave here.

812
00:34:35,480 --> 00:34:37,900
I added, because it was important to say it out loud.

813
00:34:38,340 --> 00:34:38,780
To breathe.

814
00:34:39,480 --> 00:34:39,740
Stay.

815
00:34:40,300 --> 00:34:40,740
He said.

816
00:34:40,740 --> 00:34:41,460
Low.

817
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:43,380
The house is yours, too.

818
00:34:43,620 --> 00:34:44,580
The house wasn't mine.

819
00:34:45,040 --> 00:34:47,500
The house belonged to a surname that had killed my father,

820
00:34:47,960 --> 00:34:49,560
through a man who still walked free.

821
00:34:50,120 --> 00:34:50,560
Paternal.

822
00:34:51,140 --> 00:34:53,740
Sitting at meeting tables with Evern on Tuesday mornings,

823
00:34:54,320 --> 00:34:55,800
probably with coffee and cookies.

824
00:34:56,340 --> 00:34:59,540
But at that moment, I didn't have the strength to correct the sentence.

825
00:35:00,040 --> 00:35:02,720
I had the rest of my father's tape somewhere in the world.

826
00:35:03,220 --> 00:35:06,900
A Malvani mother who had agreed to sleep far from her own home out of fear.

827
00:35:06,900 --> 00:35:11,580
And the name Masimo Grell, pulsing behind my eyes like a light that wouldn't turn off

828
00:35:11,580 --> 00:35:11,940
no.

829
00:35:12,220 --> 00:35:13,620
Matter how much I tried.

830
00:35:14,120 --> 00:35:14,940
I got up.

831
00:35:15,240 --> 00:35:16,480
I walked to the guest room.

832
00:35:16,880 --> 00:35:20,100
I stopped in the doorway, hand on the frame and looked back.

833
00:35:20,560 --> 00:35:22,540
Evern was in the same position on the couch.

834
00:35:23,040 --> 00:35:26,280
The shoulders lowered for the first time in three months of penthouse,

835
00:35:26,540 --> 00:35:29,600
and shared dinners and silences that were good because they were chosen.

836
00:35:30,120 --> 00:35:31,880
Now the lowered shoulders weren't rest.

837
00:35:32,260 --> 00:35:35,000
They were the weight of an inheritance he hadn't asked for,

838
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:37,860
and that someone had spent decades building on his shoulders

839
00:35:37,860 --> 00:35:40,280
without him knowing the real price.

840
00:35:40,920 --> 00:35:42,680
Masimo, I said out loud,

841
00:35:43,160 --> 00:35:46,820
because the first time needed to be between the two of us before anything else.

842
00:35:47,340 --> 00:35:48,820
Masimo, he repeated,

843
00:35:49,380 --> 00:35:53,080
with the same voice of someone confirming a sentence he already knew was coming.

844
00:35:53,500 --> 00:35:56,500
It was at that instant that his phone rang on the coffee table.

845
00:35:56,920 --> 00:35:58,640
We both looked at the same time,

846
00:35:58,960 --> 00:36:00,200
an involuntary reflex,

847
00:36:00,820 --> 00:36:03,140
as if the whole apartment had held its breath together.

848
00:36:03,140 --> 00:36:05,660
The screen lit up with the cold late night light.

849
00:36:06,020 --> 00:36:08,120
The name rose in clear letters on the display,

850
00:36:08,620 --> 00:36:10,780
as if it were a joke no one in the room had authorized.

851
00:36:11,420 --> 00:36:13,420
Masimo, Evern looked at me,

852
00:36:13,720 --> 00:36:14,640
I looked at him.

853
00:36:14,900 --> 00:36:16,940
He answered without bringing the phone to his face,

854
00:36:17,280 --> 00:36:20,540
on speaker, his thumb firm and motionless on the coffee table.

855
00:36:21,020 --> 00:36:22,920
The voice came sweet, slow,

856
00:36:23,540 --> 00:36:25,440
an Italian first and then in English,

857
00:36:25,960 --> 00:36:30,240
with that precise tenderness of someone calling to ask whether his son had slept well,

858
00:36:30,680 --> 00:36:31,940
and whether he'd eaten anything.

859
00:36:31,940 --> 00:36:32,860
Evern,

860
00:36:33,300 --> 00:36:34,180
figlio mio,

861
00:36:34,560 --> 00:36:35,840
your mother didn't come home.

862
00:36:36,300 --> 00:36:36,920
I got worried.

863
00:36:37,500 --> 00:36:39,160
Would you happen to know where she is?

864
00:36:44,440 --> 00:36:46,660
The cemetery that Monday morning was nearly empty.

865
00:36:47,060 --> 00:36:49,540
The sky had that washed out light of late spring.

866
00:36:50,060 --> 00:36:53,360
The kind that looks faded but burns your eyes if you look too long.

867
00:36:53,800 --> 00:36:57,500
And the wind came off the lake with the smell of still water and damp grass.

868
00:36:57,720 --> 00:36:59,560
I walked alone down the side lane,

869
00:36:59,900 --> 00:37:02,240
with a small bouquet of white daisies in my hand,

870
00:37:02,600 --> 00:37:05,760
because daisies were what my father always bought when he came home from work,

871
00:37:05,760 --> 00:37:08,540
with the excuse that he didn't have money for roses.

872
00:37:09,060 --> 00:37:11,120
He'd arrive home with the flowers a little crushed.

873
00:37:11,620 --> 00:37:13,160
The stems still slick with water,

874
00:37:13,680 --> 00:37:17,140
and put them in the jar by the kitchen sink as if that were enough for the whole week.

875
00:37:17,460 --> 00:37:18,560
It always was.

876
00:37:18,800 --> 00:37:19,860
His headstone was clean.

877
00:37:20,460 --> 00:37:21,480
I came twice a year.

878
00:37:21,920 --> 00:37:22,560
Always quick.

879
00:37:22,980 --> 00:37:24,180
Always without saying much.

880
00:37:24,500 --> 00:37:28,920
That morning, I crouched and took more time arranging the flowers than I needed to.

881
00:37:29,300 --> 00:37:30,980
Separating the stems one by one,

882
00:37:31,500 --> 00:37:33,000
straightening what was already straight.

883
00:37:33,500 --> 00:37:35,640
My hands needed something to do while I gathered

884
00:37:35,640 --> 00:37:36,280
the words.

885
00:37:36,900 --> 00:37:37,940
I didn't know dad.

886
00:37:38,360 --> 00:37:39,560
My voice came out low.

887
00:37:39,860 --> 00:37:40,520
Without theater.

888
00:37:41,140 --> 00:37:42,160
There was no one nearby.

889
00:37:42,720 --> 00:37:43,420
I could cry.

890
00:37:43,860 --> 00:37:46,680
It took me a few seconds to realize I wasn't going to.

891
00:37:46,980 --> 00:37:49,840
For 22 years I called you the man who left us early.

892
00:37:50,220 --> 00:37:53,940
For 22 years, I put on your account the bill's mom paid alone.

893
00:37:54,400 --> 00:37:58,400
For 22 years, I explained you from a distance to others,

894
00:37:58,920 --> 00:38:00,140
as if you'd had no choice.

895
00:38:00,680 --> 00:38:04,040
I ran my thumb over the letter C of the surname and graved in the stone.

896
00:38:04,040 --> 00:38:05,580
The surface was cold.

897
00:38:06,160 --> 00:38:07,300
Even in the morning sun.

898
00:38:07,780 --> 00:38:08,700
You had a choice.

899
00:38:09,240 --> 00:38:10,260
You chose us.

900
00:38:10,560 --> 00:38:13,500
I only found out too late to thank you the way I wanted to.

901
00:38:13,800 --> 00:38:15,460
I stayed crouched another minute.

902
00:38:15,900 --> 00:38:17,160
The wind stirred the daisies.

903
00:38:17,800 --> 00:38:20,860
The anger when it came was small and clear.

904
00:38:21,320 --> 00:38:23,460
Without smudges, it wasn't at him.

905
00:38:23,800 --> 00:38:28,380
It was at the man who had decided for both of them silently for years.

906
00:38:29,000 --> 00:38:33,220
Using the name of a father that wasn't his to protect a power that should never have existed.

907
00:38:33,220 --> 00:38:35,280
I'm going to take care of this.

908
00:38:35,500 --> 00:38:39,000
I said, I don't know how yet, but I will.

909
00:38:40,100 --> 00:38:40,760
I stood up.

910
00:38:41,140 --> 00:38:42,100
The wind passed again.

911
00:38:42,580 --> 00:38:47,080
I wiped my hands on my pants and walked down the lane toward the gate without looking back.

912
00:38:47,440 --> 00:38:51,320
Dario was waiting for me, leaning against the black car at the bend in the street.

913
00:38:51,780 --> 00:38:55,940
With the posture of someone who'd learned to take up the least space possible in any scenario.

914
00:38:56,580 --> 00:38:58,300
Dark suit even in early spring.

915
00:38:58,720 --> 00:38:59,360
Sun glasses.

916
00:38:59,940 --> 00:39:01,880
His tie loosened exactly one millimeter.

917
00:39:01,880 --> 00:39:05,320
Which for him probably counted as a concession to the season.

918
00:39:05,720 --> 00:39:07,680
Sarai was in the passenger seat of her car.

919
00:39:08,100 --> 00:39:08,980
Behind his.

920
00:39:09,240 --> 00:39:10,180
With the window open.

921
00:39:10,680 --> 00:39:12,760
Enter hair pinned in a careless twist.

922
00:39:13,260 --> 00:39:17,260
Reading something on her phone with the expression of someone pretending not to be paying attention

923
00:39:17,260 --> 00:39:19,440
to absolutely everything around her.

924
00:39:19,460 --> 00:39:20,860
I wasn't expecting you.

925
00:39:21,020 --> 00:39:21,440
I said.

926
00:39:21,960 --> 00:39:22,440
He asked.

927
00:39:23,020 --> 00:39:23,700
Dario answered.

928
00:39:24,200 --> 00:39:25,520
In his usual half voice.

929
00:39:25,960 --> 00:39:27,200
Controlled and without inflection.

930
00:39:27,880 --> 00:39:30,640
I figured it'd be simpler for me to bring it than to send it.

931
00:39:30,640 --> 00:39:31,720
He opened the trunk.

932
00:39:32,120 --> 00:39:33,780
He took out a sealed cardboard box.

933
00:39:34,180 --> 00:39:34,820
Medium sized.

934
00:39:35,400 --> 00:39:35,900
No label.

935
00:39:36,520 --> 00:39:40,540
Packing tape run three times around the edges as if the contents demanded extra care.

936
00:39:40,860 --> 00:39:44,940
It weighed enough that both his arms compensated for the weight for an instant before adjusting.

937
00:39:45,620 --> 00:39:46,660
Everything is here.

938
00:39:47,080 --> 00:39:47,600
He said.

939
00:39:48,040 --> 00:39:49,320
Everything he has.

940
00:39:49,660 --> 00:39:50,480
I looked at the box.

941
00:39:51,080 --> 00:39:51,520
At Dario.

942
00:39:52,180 --> 00:39:52,820
At the sky.

943
00:39:53,300 --> 00:39:55,660
Which still had that washed out light that chose nothing.

944
00:39:56,120 --> 00:39:57,160
Did he send a note?

945
00:39:57,160 --> 00:40:00,360
Dario took from the inner pocket of his jacket a folded card.

946
00:40:00,940 --> 00:40:02,420
And handed it to me without ceremony.

947
00:40:03,140 --> 00:40:04,460
Evern's handwriting was straight.

948
00:40:04,960 --> 00:40:05,260
Firm.

949
00:40:05,860 --> 00:40:06,520
Without flourish.

950
00:40:07,200 --> 00:40:09,320
The capital letters a bit larger than necessary.

951
00:40:09,860 --> 00:40:11,840
As if they were holding something behind them.

952
00:40:12,020 --> 00:40:12,580
You decide.

953
00:40:13,220 --> 00:40:14,120
I won't touch it.

954
00:40:14,360 --> 00:40:15,920
I put the card in my coat pocket.

955
00:40:16,400 --> 00:40:17,320
Close to my chest.

956
00:40:17,780 --> 00:40:21,080
Surai got out of the car with two cups of coffee and handed me one.

957
00:40:21,500 --> 00:40:25,460
Looking at me for a second with that silence she used when she didn't want me to know she was

958
00:40:25,460 --> 00:40:25,780
worried.

959
00:40:25,780 --> 00:40:31,220
Her glance passed quickly over Dario before returning to him with the speed of someone who tried not to

960
00:40:31,220 --> 00:40:32,940
look and hadn't managed to.

961
00:40:33,440 --> 00:40:33,940
Nice suit.

962
00:40:34,480 --> 00:40:35,160
Surai said.

963
00:40:35,600 --> 00:40:36,640
With a slanted smile.

964
00:40:37,240 --> 00:40:39,120
In the middle of a Chicago summer.

965
00:40:39,640 --> 00:40:41,780
Who introduced you to summer around here creature.

966
00:40:42,520 --> 00:40:44,520
Dario turned his face slightly toward her.

967
00:40:44,720 --> 00:40:46,540
The dark glasses didn't let his eyes show.

968
00:40:46,980 --> 00:40:49,740
But the pause before his answer was long enough to be intentional.

969
00:40:50,380 --> 00:40:51,380
Do you feel hot?

970
00:40:51,860 --> 00:40:52,600
Surai pressed.

971
00:40:53,000 --> 00:40:54,320
Amused by her own advance.

972
00:40:54,320 --> 00:40:57,600
Do you always ask questions about other people's clothes?

973
00:40:58,240 --> 00:40:59,280
Dario shot back.

974
00:40:59,600 --> 00:41:00,780
Voice dry as paper.

975
00:41:01,360 --> 00:41:03,440
Surai laughed before the end of her own answer.

976
00:41:03,940 --> 00:41:05,960
The kind of laugh that doesn't wait for permission.

977
00:41:06,680 --> 00:41:06,940
Always.

978
00:41:07,560 --> 00:41:08,120
She said.

979
00:41:08,540 --> 00:41:11,240
It's my way of keeping my sanity in the middle of all this.

980
00:41:11,620 --> 00:41:13,860
They I'd each other for a second longer than necessary.

981
00:41:14,440 --> 00:41:17,900
It was the only thing in that whole morning that pulled a smile out of me.

982
00:41:18,340 --> 00:41:20,940
Surai took the box from Dario's hands without asking.

983
00:41:20,940 --> 00:41:25,320
As if the weight were an offense she resolved before he could try to carry it back.

984
00:41:25,740 --> 00:41:27,120
Said it in the trunk of our car.

985
00:41:27,640 --> 00:41:29,540
And slammed the lid with the palm of her hand.

986
00:41:30,060 --> 00:41:30,600
Let's go.

987
00:41:31,020 --> 00:41:31,980
She said to me.

988
00:41:32,340 --> 00:41:35,540
Ignoring Dario with the precision of someone very aware of his presence.

989
00:41:36,080 --> 00:41:37,980
There's a hotel office waiting for you.

990
00:41:38,260 --> 00:41:39,500
Dario nodded to me slightly.

991
00:41:40,120 --> 00:41:40,860
Not to her.

992
00:41:41,140 --> 00:41:42,460
He got into his own car.

993
00:41:42,780 --> 00:41:45,080
With the same contained gesture as always.

994
00:41:45,460 --> 00:41:46,880
And I had to look the other way.

995
00:41:47,120 --> 00:41:48,360
So I wouldn't smile again.

996
00:41:48,360 --> 00:41:52,300
The hotel's events office smelled of warm paper and old flowers.

997
00:41:52,900 --> 00:41:57,480
The residual scent of two arrangements I hadn't had changed the week before.

998
00:41:57,780 --> 00:41:59,840
It was the same room where I'd kept for months.

999
00:42:00,320 --> 00:42:02,040
The folder with the evidence against Calvin.

1000
00:42:02,680 --> 00:42:04,000
The same dark wood shelf.

1001
00:42:04,460 --> 00:42:09,060
The same lamp with the butter-colored shade that had needed a stronger bulb for at least two years.

1002
00:42:09,380 --> 00:42:12,960
The same door with the lock that required a shove of the shoulder to close properly.

1003
00:42:13,500 --> 00:42:15,480
I set Evron's box on top of the desk.

1004
00:42:15,480 --> 00:42:19,740
The same gesture as before, countless times with Calvin's folder.

1005
00:42:20,360 --> 00:42:22,840
The different weight, the completely different feeling.

1006
00:42:23,500 --> 00:42:24,320
I opened it.

1007
00:42:24,660 --> 00:42:28,900
Inside, organized into subfolders numbered in Evron's handwriting on the labels.

1008
00:42:29,380 --> 00:42:30,660
Was the entire empire.

1009
00:42:31,220 --> 00:42:33,220
Casino contracts with coded clauses,

1010
00:42:33,760 --> 00:42:35,860
laundering schemes that ran through charity events.

1011
00:42:36,420 --> 00:42:38,580
At least four of them at hotels I knew by name.

1012
00:42:39,080 --> 00:42:43,660
Names of council members, of two mayors, of a retired federal judge,

1013
00:42:43,660 --> 00:42:47,540
lists of monthly payments with dates and initials beside each entry.

1014
00:42:48,280 --> 00:42:49,720
meticulous as clean bookkeeping.

1015
00:42:50,300 --> 00:42:52,280
As if Evron had spent the last months building.

1016
00:42:53,060 --> 00:42:54,920
In silence and without telling me anything.

1017
00:42:55,540 --> 00:42:57,540
The very dossier against himself.

1018
00:42:57,920 --> 00:43:01,820
In a subfolder at the back, separated from the others by a blue tab.

1019
00:43:02,360 --> 00:43:05,900
Three thin envelopes with the label and tarot cross written by hand.

1020
00:43:06,460 --> 00:43:07,320
Original documents.

1021
00:43:08,060 --> 00:43:10,120
Copies of internal reports from the time.

1022
00:43:10,620 --> 00:43:13,220
The complete transcription of a third witnesses testimony

1023
00:43:13,220 --> 00:43:14,080
that confirmed.

1024
00:43:14,840 --> 00:43:15,660
Point by point.

1025
00:43:16,160 --> 00:43:17,720
What Bruna had said the night before.

1026
00:43:18,320 --> 00:43:21,200
I stayed looking at the envelopes longer than I expected to need.

1027
00:43:21,620 --> 00:43:25,500
I held in my hands enough to clear my father's name before any camera in the country.

1028
00:43:26,040 --> 00:43:29,120
And enough to send Evron to prison for the next 20 odd years.

1029
00:43:29,600 --> 00:43:30,720
I sat in the chair.

1030
00:43:31,140 --> 00:43:33,320
Surai sat on the edge of the desk at my side.

1031
00:43:33,600 --> 00:43:34,180
Without joking.

1032
00:43:34,840 --> 00:43:36,580
Without filling the silence with anything.

1033
00:43:36,920 --> 00:43:39,700
She stayed there while I leaped through each subfolder.

1034
00:43:40,020 --> 00:43:40,300
Slowly.

1035
00:43:41,020 --> 00:43:42,940
Reading enough to understand what I was holding

1036
00:43:42,940 --> 00:43:45,160
without needing to read it all to know the weight.

1037
00:43:45,660 --> 00:43:47,280
You don't have to decide today.

1038
00:43:47,620 --> 00:43:48,280
Surai said.

1039
00:43:48,660 --> 00:43:49,520
After a long while.

1040
00:43:50,060 --> 00:43:50,420
I know.

1041
00:43:50,860 --> 00:43:52,440
But you're going to decide today.

1042
00:43:52,900 --> 00:43:53,480
I know.

1043
00:43:53,820 --> 00:43:55,760
She put her hand over mine for two seconds.

1044
00:43:56,360 --> 00:43:57,320
Not a third.

1045
00:43:57,540 --> 00:43:59,480
Which would have been too much for both of us.

1046
00:43:59,800 --> 00:44:01,300
I've known you since you were 22.

1047
00:44:01,720 --> 00:44:01,920
No.

1048
00:44:02,100 --> 00:44:03,980
You don't decide anything in an office.

1049
00:44:04,480 --> 00:44:05,540
You decide over coffee.

1050
00:44:06,120 --> 00:44:10,160
That was why I ended up inside the cafe in the hotel's neighborhood and hour later.

1051
00:44:10,160 --> 00:44:15,080
With the box closed again under the table and the smell of espresso and cinnamon mixed with

1052
00:44:15,080 --> 00:44:18,100
the low sound of music no one was really listening to.

1053
00:44:18,420 --> 00:44:22,580
The view in the mirror behind the counter gave me back my face without makeup for the first time in

1054
00:44:22,580 --> 00:44:22,960
weeks.

1055
00:44:23,440 --> 00:44:24,480
I looked at the reflection.

1056
00:44:25,180 --> 00:44:29,360
The reflection looked back at me with the same absent calm of someone who's already

1057
00:44:29,360 --> 00:44:31,540
decided and hasn't yet told her own body.

1058
00:44:32,060 --> 00:44:33,920
There was no longer the woman from the altar.

1059
00:44:34,380 --> 00:44:36,060
There was no longer the radio headline.

1060
00:44:36,660 --> 00:44:37,840
There was just me.

1061
00:44:38,180 --> 00:44:39,400
Over a cup of black coffee.

1062
00:44:39,900 --> 00:44:43,920
Deciding the rest of my own story with my hands wrapped around the warm cup.

1063
00:44:44,420 --> 00:44:45,380
I thought about my father.

1064
00:44:45,880 --> 00:44:47,140
I thought about everin.

1065
00:44:47,340 --> 00:44:48,460
I thought about myself.

1066
00:44:48,960 --> 00:44:51,820
In the exact order the things needed to be thought about.

1067
00:44:52,180 --> 00:44:53,060
I stood up.

1068
00:44:53,340 --> 00:44:58,020
I went back to the penthouse in the late afternoon with the box again in the passenger seat

1069
00:44:58,020 --> 00:45:01,400
and the sun going down over the lake in tones of old copper.

1070
00:45:02,400 --> 00:45:06,600
The kind of light that makes everything more beautiful and heavier at the same time.

1071
00:45:07,160 --> 00:45:12,180
I rode up in the private elevator in silence with my own reflection accompanying me in the

1072
00:45:12,180 --> 00:45:14,480
mirrored elevator door until the floor closed.

1073
00:45:15,380 --> 00:45:18,460
I opened the door with the key he'd given me three months earlier.

1074
00:45:19,340 --> 00:45:21,600
I've ran with standing in the living room facing the window,

1075
00:45:22,200 --> 00:45:23,420
phone in his lowered hand.

1076
00:45:23,860 --> 00:45:25,800
He hadn't heard the door when he turned.

1077
00:45:26,320 --> 00:45:27,420
His eyes were different.

1078
00:45:27,940 --> 00:45:29,720
With a stillness that wasn't calm.

1079
00:45:30,180 --> 00:45:34,000
It was the kind of stillness of someone who had just received news they'd waited their

1080
00:45:34,000 --> 00:45:36,600
whole life for, without knowing they were waiting.

1081
00:45:37,180 --> 00:45:42,540
Massimo, he said simply, as if the name weighed enough not to need anything else around it.

1082
00:45:42,720 --> 00:45:43,540
He took my mother.

1083
00:45:44,000 --> 00:45:45,460
I stopped in the middle of the room.

1084
00:45:45,980 --> 00:45:49,240
When, 40 minutes ago, he called just now.

1085
00:45:49,520 --> 00:45:51,680
He once the box burned in 24 hours.

1086
00:45:52,140 --> 00:45:52,460
Filmed.

1087
00:45:52,960 --> 00:45:54,180
In exchange for my mother.

1088
00:45:54,620 --> 00:45:56,300
I set the box on the coffee table.

1089
00:45:56,900 --> 00:45:57,960
Between the two of us.

1090
00:45:58,300 --> 00:46:02,140
The sound of the wood receiving the weight filled the room for one full second.

1091
00:46:02,140 --> 00:46:03,860
Clean and definitive.

1092
00:46:04,640 --> 00:46:05,600
Ever end looked at the box.

1093
00:46:06,140 --> 00:46:07,120
He looked at me.

1094
00:46:07,260 --> 00:46:09,640
He said nothing for a while I didn't try to shorten.

1095
00:46:10,200 --> 00:46:11,280
I sat on the couch.

1096
00:46:11,740 --> 00:46:13,780
He sat in the armchair across from me.

1097
00:46:14,000 --> 00:46:17,220
The box between us like a third body neither of us invited.

1098
00:46:17,820 --> 00:46:18,860
But that was there.

1099
00:46:19,400 --> 00:46:20,620
Present and motionless.

1100
00:46:20,980 --> 00:46:21,900
Demanding an answer.

1101
00:46:22,440 --> 00:46:23,940
The silence lasted three minutes.

1102
00:46:24,520 --> 00:46:26,380
I didn't count because I needed to measure.

1103
00:46:26,860 --> 00:46:29,780
I counted because it was the first time in 22 years

1104
00:46:29,780 --> 00:46:33,480
that two entire surnames, cross and malvani.

1105
00:46:34,060 --> 00:46:37,620
Sad in the same room without anyone trying to defend themselves from the other.

1106
00:46:37,980 --> 00:46:40,160
His fingers moved slowly over the tabletop,

1107
00:46:40,640 --> 00:46:41,720
without apparent purpose.

1108
00:46:42,340 --> 00:46:43,960
Until they reached the edge of the box.

1109
00:46:44,500 --> 00:46:46,140
My fingers came to the other end.

1110
00:46:46,620 --> 00:46:47,540
Almost without deciding.

1111
00:46:48,180 --> 00:46:49,820
Our thumbs came close to touching.

1112
00:46:50,200 --> 00:46:51,000
They stopped there.

1113
00:46:51,380 --> 00:46:53,340
Less than a centimeter apart without touching.

1114
00:46:53,800 --> 00:46:55,000
We're not going to burn it.

1115
00:46:55,280 --> 00:46:55,720
I said.

1116
00:46:56,180 --> 00:46:59,760
He lifted his eyes with a slowness that told me he already knew I was going to say

1117
00:47:00,240 --> 00:47:01,680
and was waiting anyway.

1118
00:47:02,140 --> 00:47:03,980
We're going to record him saying it.

1119
00:47:04,340 --> 00:47:04,740
I finished.

1120
00:47:05,380 --> 00:47:07,260
Everin stayed looking at me for a while.

1121
00:47:07,600 --> 00:47:08,760
Without asking how.

1122
00:47:09,120 --> 00:47:10,160
Without asking why.

1123
00:47:10,580 --> 00:47:11,240
Just looking.

1124
00:47:11,860 --> 00:47:14,900
In that way he'd had since the first time backstage at the hotel.

1125
00:47:15,540 --> 00:47:16,120
Months earlier.

1126
00:47:16,680 --> 00:47:19,880
When he scanned the room's three exits before scanning me.

1127
00:47:20,120 --> 00:47:22,140
And then completely forgot the exits.

1128
00:47:22,800 --> 00:47:26,280
When he asked, there's day night at the hotel.

1129
00:47:26,660 --> 00:47:29,240
I'll set up a private donors event in the smaller ballroom.

1130
00:47:29,240 --> 00:47:30,880
His allies will be invited.

1131
00:47:31,420 --> 00:47:33,740
He'll come because he always comes to the hotel's events.

1132
00:47:34,080 --> 00:47:34,880
I lead it.

1133
00:47:35,100 --> 00:47:35,440
You wait.

1134
00:47:36,100 --> 00:47:36,420
Dario.

1135
00:47:37,040 --> 00:47:38,920
Dario coordinates parallel security.

1136
00:47:39,660 --> 00:47:41,020
Sir I works the catering.

1137
00:47:41,320 --> 00:47:43,060
I talk to Massimo in a side room.

1138
00:47:43,540 --> 00:47:44,220
Sealing microphones.

1139
00:47:44,980 --> 00:47:47,640
The old ones still installed from last year's retrofit.

1140
00:47:48,040 --> 00:47:48,840
He nodded once.

1141
00:47:49,460 --> 00:47:49,720
Slowly.

1142
00:47:50,420 --> 00:47:51,120
And my mother.

1143
00:47:51,700 --> 00:47:54,380
The police move in on the warehouse when the confession is closed.

1144
00:47:54,940 --> 00:47:55,740
You go in first.

1145
00:47:56,040 --> 00:47:56,400
Alone.

1146
00:47:56,400 --> 00:47:58,880
To make sure she's alive when the door opens.

1147
00:47:59,380 --> 00:48:01,020
He looked at me for a long while.

1148
00:48:01,340 --> 00:48:05,380
His eyes running over my face as if searching for a fracture in the plan or in me.

1149
00:48:05,660 --> 00:48:07,180
You know what you're asking me to do.

1150
00:48:07,560 --> 00:48:08,100
I know.

1151
00:48:08,380 --> 00:48:09,440
I'm going to lose everything.

1152
00:48:10,000 --> 00:48:10,520
I know.

1153
00:48:10,920 --> 00:48:12,540
I'm not asking you to give up.

1154
00:48:12,780 --> 00:48:13,300
He said.

1155
00:48:13,760 --> 00:48:15,640
And his voice came out lower than I expected.

1156
00:48:16,180 --> 00:48:18,020
With a layer underneath that wasn't weakness.

1157
00:48:18,640 --> 00:48:19,440
But was close.

1158
00:48:19,920 --> 00:48:22,280
I'm asking whether you truly know what it means to me.

1159
00:48:22,540 --> 00:48:23,420
I stood up.

1160
00:48:23,620 --> 00:48:24,960
I rounded the table slowly.

1161
00:48:24,960 --> 00:48:29,280
I stopped in front of him and put my hand on his face for the first time in three days.

1162
00:48:29,740 --> 00:48:31,340
The skin was cold near the temple.

1163
00:48:31,880 --> 00:48:32,880
Warm near the jaw.

1164
00:48:33,300 --> 00:48:37,080
He closed his eyes with the slowness of someone who had forgotten what it was like to receive

1165
00:48:37,080 --> 00:48:39,500
that kind of touch without having to prepare himself.

1166
00:48:39,860 --> 00:48:40,420
I know.

1167
00:48:40,860 --> 00:48:41,220
I repeated.

1168
00:48:41,940 --> 00:48:45,620
And I'm not going to burn my father's truth to preserve your father's empire.

1169
00:48:46,080 --> 00:48:47,880
And you're not going to ask me to.

1170
00:48:48,100 --> 00:48:49,000
He opened his eyes.

1171
00:48:49,480 --> 00:48:49,960
I won't.

1172
00:48:50,380 --> 00:48:50,840
He said.

1173
00:48:51,240 --> 00:48:52,580
I took my hand away slowly.

1174
00:48:53,120 --> 00:48:54,220
I went back to the couch.

1175
00:48:54,220 --> 00:48:56,940
I picked up the events notebook from the coffee table.

1176
00:48:57,500 --> 00:49:01,040
Opened it to the first blank page and started writing the guest list.

1177
00:49:01,480 --> 00:49:02,540
The names came easily.

1178
00:49:02,960 --> 00:49:03,620
From memory.

1179
00:49:04,140 --> 00:49:06,240
As if I'd rehearsed them without knowing for weeks.

1180
00:49:06,900 --> 00:49:07,780
Everin stood up.

1181
00:49:08,040 --> 00:49:09,000
He walked to the window.

1182
00:49:09,400 --> 00:49:10,940
He stayed with his back to me.

1183
00:49:11,240 --> 00:49:12,640
Hands crossed behind him.

1184
00:49:12,980 --> 00:49:15,760
Looking at the lake darkening with the last light of the afternoon.

1185
00:49:16,440 --> 00:49:18,800
The horizon dissolving into blue and gray.

1186
00:49:19,200 --> 00:49:19,520
Thursday.

1187
00:49:20,120 --> 00:49:20,740
He said.

1188
00:49:20,740 --> 00:49:21,320
Low.

1189
00:49:21,880 --> 00:49:25,400
Like someone sealing a pact with himself out loud just to make it real.

1190
00:49:25,760 --> 00:49:26,060
Thursday.

1191
00:49:26,760 --> 00:49:27,240
I confirmed.

1192
00:49:27,900 --> 00:49:29,460
Without lifting my head from the notebook.

1193
00:49:30,000 --> 00:49:33,080
The box stayed on top of the coffee table between us.

1194
00:49:33,320 --> 00:49:35,240
With the packing tape on the edges intact.

1195
00:49:35,720 --> 00:49:37,100
And the names inside it waiting.

1196
00:49:37,880 --> 00:49:44,220
Neither of us touched it that night.

1197
00:49:44,640 --> 00:49:48,900
The hotel's smaller ballroom was half the size of the main ballroom and got double my attention.

1198
00:49:49,500 --> 00:49:50,860
I knew every exit.

1199
00:49:51,440 --> 00:49:52,200
Every outlet.

1200
00:49:52,760 --> 00:49:54,560
Every loose screw in the baseboard.

1201
00:49:54,560 --> 00:49:58,840
I'd chosen that space because it was the only one in the hotel where I knew,

1202
00:49:59,060 --> 00:50:03,820
by heart, where the sealing microphones from the renovation three years earlier were.

1203
00:50:04,140 --> 00:50:06,040
The ones that had never been uninstalled.

1204
00:50:06,420 --> 00:50:08,680
Because no one on the board remembered they existed.

1205
00:50:09,280 --> 00:50:09,760
I remembered.

1206
00:50:10,460 --> 00:50:15,100
I arrived at six in the afternoon with the private donors events spreadsheet under my arm,

1207
00:50:15,240 --> 00:50:16,240
as if it were real.

1208
00:50:16,760 --> 00:50:20,560
So I was already setting up the buffet with the calm of someone who'd never put a

1209
00:50:20,560 --> 00:50:21,960
spy earpiece in her ear.

1210
00:50:21,960 --> 00:50:24,460
At least that was what she wanted to look like.

1211
00:50:24,880 --> 00:50:26,680
A canna pay is a bladed weapon.

1212
00:50:27,100 --> 00:50:28,760
She said quietly when I passed.

1213
00:50:29,260 --> 00:50:32,860
Whoever invented catering was never at an event with this kind of person.

1214
00:50:33,340 --> 00:50:34,060
Are you okay?

1215
00:50:34,600 --> 00:50:35,280
I'm great.

1216
00:50:35,620 --> 00:50:39,520
I'm organizing a crime against a mafia advisor while I serve mushroom tartlets.

1217
00:50:40,060 --> 00:50:41,400
What kind of question is that?

1218
00:50:41,760 --> 00:50:43,700
She laughed before finishing the sentence.

1219
00:50:44,240 --> 00:50:44,780
So did I.

1220
00:50:45,260 --> 00:50:46,480
For the first time all day.

1221
00:50:46,860 --> 00:50:47,920
It was only a second.

1222
00:50:48,340 --> 00:50:49,680
But I needed that second.

1223
00:50:49,680 --> 00:50:53,300
Daria appeared through the service door in the same black suit as always,

1224
00:50:53,660 --> 00:50:54,740
and two small bags.

1225
00:50:55,240 --> 00:50:59,660
He walked over to us with the manner of someone entering the ballroom for the 30th time that day,

1226
00:51:00,020 --> 00:51:01,620
even though he'd entered for the first.

1227
00:51:02,120 --> 00:51:05,180
He held out a small earpiece, the color of syri skin,

1228
00:51:05,740 --> 00:51:07,280
and a microphone the size of a lintel.

1229
00:51:08,440 --> 00:51:10,220
Ms. Dom. Ms. Dom.

1230
00:51:10,660 --> 00:51:12,660
Surai repeated, pretending to be impressed.

1231
00:51:13,240 --> 00:51:13,560
Great.

1232
00:51:14,100 --> 00:51:15,720
Now I'm officially a spy actress.

1233
00:51:16,200 --> 00:51:17,380
Can I put that on my resume?

1234
00:51:17,380 --> 00:51:19,900
Daria looked at her for two and a half seconds.

1235
00:51:20,460 --> 00:51:20,880
You can.

1236
00:51:21,360 --> 00:51:22,140
That was all.

1237
00:51:22,520 --> 00:51:24,640
Surai opened her mouth, closed it,

1238
00:51:24,900 --> 00:51:27,180
and filed the smile off to the side of her face.

1239
00:51:27,660 --> 00:51:28,420
I saw it.

1240
00:51:28,760 --> 00:51:30,040
She saw that I saw it.

1241
00:51:30,440 --> 00:51:31,920
Daria pretended not to see,

1242
00:51:32,260 --> 00:51:35,500
and still waited a millimeter longer than necessary before turning to me.

1243
00:51:35,840 --> 00:51:37,280
The ceiling microphones are active.

1244
00:51:37,780 --> 00:51:40,760
The police move in when you give the signal with the agreed upon phrase.

1245
00:51:41,280 --> 00:51:42,820
I think the night's going to run long.

1246
00:51:43,280 --> 00:51:44,740
I repeated, exactly.

1247
00:51:44,740 --> 00:51:48,160
Everyone came in through the service hallway at seven on the dot.

1248
00:51:48,600 --> 00:51:49,700
He didn't look at me first.

1249
00:51:50,140 --> 00:51:51,060
He looked at the exits.

1250
00:51:51,720 --> 00:51:53,320
The old habit I now knew how to read,

1251
00:51:53,860 --> 00:51:56,080
and only then met my eyes across the ballroom.

1252
00:51:56,500 --> 00:51:58,840
His hand went down to his pocket and stayed there.

1253
00:51:59,120 --> 00:51:59,640
Not the ring.

1254
00:52:00,060 --> 00:52:02,100
I'd already noticed that the family ring had disappeared

1255
00:52:02,100 --> 00:52:03,840
from his finger since the day before.

1256
00:52:04,240 --> 00:52:05,320
He hadn't said anything.

1257
00:52:05,840 --> 00:52:06,600
Neither had I.

1258
00:52:06,980 --> 00:52:08,420
Massimo arrived at seven 15.

1259
00:52:08,980 --> 00:52:09,740
He came smiling.

1260
00:52:10,240 --> 00:52:13,720
In the beige cashmere coat I'd already seen in a photo at the penthouse.

1261
00:52:13,720 --> 00:52:16,940
One of the few in which everyone was a child in his arms.

1262
00:52:17,460 --> 00:52:20,820
He greeted three donors who weren't donors as if greeting distant relatives.

1263
00:52:21,440 --> 00:52:24,380
He kissed my hand as if I were the hostess of a family tea.

1264
00:52:24,760 --> 00:52:25,160
Noelia.

1265
00:52:25,640 --> 00:52:27,280
He said, what a pleasure.

1266
00:52:27,980 --> 00:52:29,780
Massimo, sit with me a moment.

1267
00:52:30,220 --> 00:52:32,640
I want to walk you through the setup before the others arrive.

1268
00:52:33,100 --> 00:52:33,880
Of course, dear.

1269
00:52:34,400 --> 00:52:37,520
The word dear landed on my skin like a wet stone.

1270
00:52:38,000 --> 00:52:38,740
I didn't flinch.

1271
00:52:39,060 --> 00:52:39,680
I'd practiced.

1272
00:52:40,080 --> 00:52:41,320
I took him to the sideroom.

1273
00:52:41,320 --> 00:52:43,400
The previous manager's office.

1274
00:52:43,860 --> 00:52:46,940
Old leather couch, round table, fake chandelier.

1275
00:52:47,540 --> 00:52:49,860
The ceiling microphones were embedded in the stucco.

1276
00:52:50,440 --> 00:52:51,580
No one would look up.

1277
00:52:51,780 --> 00:52:53,180
I sat at the end of the couch.

1278
00:52:53,620 --> 00:52:57,720
He sat in the armchair across from me and crossed his legs like someone about to have lunch.

1279
00:52:58,320 --> 00:52:59,520
Ever in his tents today.

1280
00:53:00,000 --> 00:53:00,500
He began.

1281
00:53:01,060 --> 00:53:01,460
Paternal.

1282
00:53:02,000 --> 00:53:03,820
This tape business is weighing on him.

1283
00:53:04,160 --> 00:53:06,340
I know my father was involved with the old Melvani.

1284
00:53:07,020 --> 00:53:07,420
I answered.

1285
00:53:08,000 --> 00:53:08,500
He was.

1286
00:53:09,000 --> 00:53:09,780
He sighed.

1287
00:53:09,780 --> 00:53:11,980
Antara was a good man in bad circumstances.

1288
00:53:12,720 --> 00:53:13,520
It was a shame.

1289
00:53:14,020 --> 00:53:14,800
You knew him.

1290
00:53:15,060 --> 00:53:15,520
I did.

1291
00:53:16,060 --> 00:53:19,020
I was in the car with the old Melvani the night your father was killed.

1292
00:53:19,520 --> 00:53:21,560
I hadn't expected the sentence so soon.

1293
00:53:22,000 --> 00:53:24,320
I felt my pulse beat twice as hard in my throat.

1294
00:53:24,780 --> 00:53:25,540
I didn't blink.

1295
00:53:26,080 --> 00:53:26,820
You were there.

1296
00:53:27,360 --> 00:53:27,760
I repeated.

1297
00:53:28,540 --> 00:53:29,180
I was.

1298
00:53:29,700 --> 00:53:32,800
Massimo uncrossed his legs and rested his elbows on his knees.

1299
00:53:33,280 --> 00:53:34,780
You deserved to know Noelia.

1300
00:53:35,360 --> 00:53:37,440
He smiled as if he were doing a favor.

1301
00:53:37,440 --> 00:53:41,000
Your father was a sentimental man in a place where sentiment kills.

1302
00:53:41,660 --> 00:53:44,820
I resolved with the old Melvani was too cowardly to resolve.

1303
00:53:45,280 --> 00:53:46,300
You killed my father.

1304
00:53:46,840 --> 00:53:47,920
I corrected a mistake.

1305
00:53:48,500 --> 00:53:52,020
Don't expect me to apologize for something I kept standing for 20 years.

1306
00:53:52,500 --> 00:53:54,540
You would have done the same if you'd had the chance.

1307
00:53:55,060 --> 00:53:57,480
The ceiling microphones were capturing every syllable.

1308
00:53:58,100 --> 00:53:59,680
In Bruna, I asked.

1309
00:54:00,140 --> 00:54:02,040
My voice low enough that he leaned forward.

1310
00:54:02,680 --> 00:54:03,560
Where is she now?

1311
00:54:03,920 --> 00:54:04,800
In a safe place.

1312
00:54:04,800 --> 00:54:07,960
Where nothing will happen to her if Evern does as agreed.

1313
00:54:08,480 --> 00:54:10,840
You kidnapped the mother of the man who calls you father.

1314
00:54:11,400 --> 00:54:11,840
I borrowed.

1315
00:54:12,420 --> 00:54:12,860
He smiled.

1316
00:54:13,400 --> 00:54:14,800
The only leverage he has.

1317
00:54:15,240 --> 00:54:16,220
I breathed in deep.

1318
00:54:16,700 --> 00:54:17,800
I looked at the chandelier.

1319
00:54:18,280 --> 00:54:19,040
I said calmly.

1320
00:54:19,640 --> 00:54:21,340
I think the night's going to run long.

1321
00:54:21,780 --> 00:54:23,280
The sentence came out waitless.

1322
00:54:23,780 --> 00:54:25,460
Massimo didn't even register it.

1323
00:54:25,700 --> 00:54:27,260
He kept talking about the old Melvani.

1324
00:54:27,880 --> 00:54:28,580
About loyalty.

1325
00:54:29,260 --> 00:54:31,220
About how Evern would still come to understand.

1326
00:54:31,840 --> 00:54:33,080
I was no longer listening.

1327
00:54:33,080 --> 00:54:34,380
Somewhere in the hotel.

1328
00:54:35,000 --> 00:54:36,280
Dario was closing the channel.

1329
00:54:36,720 --> 00:54:37,500
Somewhere in Chicago.

1330
00:54:38,240 --> 00:54:40,740
Two federal police cars were pulling out of a garage.

1331
00:54:41,340 --> 00:54:42,580
Somewhere above our heads.

1332
00:54:43,040 --> 00:54:46,520
A fake chandelier was recording the complete confession of Massimo Grel.

1333
00:54:47,040 --> 00:54:48,640
That was when he saw my face.

1334
00:54:49,020 --> 00:54:50,540
I don't know what appeared in it.

1335
00:54:50,820 --> 00:54:52,040
Maybe the lack of fear.

1336
00:54:52,520 --> 00:54:53,760
He stood up in half a second.

1337
00:54:54,100 --> 00:54:57,660
And his hand was on my wrist while the other went to the pocket of his beige coat.

1338
00:54:58,120 --> 00:54:59,980
He knew the police already had the audio.

1339
00:55:00,480 --> 00:55:02,360
He knew he had minutes, not hours.

1340
00:55:02,360 --> 00:55:04,020
What did you do, Noelia?

1341
00:55:04,600 --> 00:55:06,640
The gun pressed against the side of my body.

1342
00:55:06,940 --> 00:55:08,480
Low, hidden by the couch.

1343
00:55:08,960 --> 00:55:10,920
I felt the cold metal through my dress.

1344
00:55:11,320 --> 00:55:12,040
I didn't scream.

1345
00:55:12,660 --> 00:55:13,660
You recorded it.

1346
00:55:13,920 --> 00:55:14,400
He said.

1347
00:55:14,860 --> 00:55:15,860
I recorded it.

1348
00:55:16,120 --> 00:55:18,360
The door of the side room opened without a sound.

1349
00:55:18,900 --> 00:55:21,220
Dario was standing in it with that half expression.

1350
00:55:21,860 --> 00:55:23,120
Less neutral than usual.

1351
00:55:23,680 --> 00:55:24,660
That he kept for emergencies.

1352
00:55:25,380 --> 00:55:26,420
He didn't look at Massimo.

1353
00:55:26,940 --> 00:55:27,880
He looked at me.

1354
00:55:28,080 --> 00:55:28,740
Miss Cross.

1355
00:55:29,360 --> 00:55:30,520
Massimo stepped back.

1356
00:55:30,860 --> 00:55:31,460
The gun lowered.

1357
00:55:31,460 --> 00:55:33,480
He let go of my wrist slowly.

1358
00:55:34,340 --> 00:55:34,780
Unhurried.

1359
00:55:35,100 --> 00:55:36,380
Calculating something else.

1360
00:55:36,800 --> 00:55:37,920
I knew what he was calculating.

1361
00:55:38,700 --> 00:55:39,440
The parking garage.

1362
00:55:40,080 --> 00:55:40,260
Runa.

1363
00:55:40,940 --> 00:55:41,280
He said.

1364
00:55:41,780 --> 00:55:45,140
And it was the only word before he left through the back door toward the service hallway.

1365
00:55:45,640 --> 00:55:46,740
Dario looked at me.

1366
00:55:46,880 --> 00:55:47,780
I shook my head.

1367
00:55:48,120 --> 00:55:49,160
He went after him.

1368
00:55:49,340 --> 00:55:51,040
I stayed in the armchair for four seconds.

1369
00:55:51,600 --> 00:55:52,080
I counted.

1370
00:55:52,700 --> 00:55:54,700
Four seconds for my pulse to return to normal.

1371
00:55:55,040 --> 00:55:56,060
Then I got up.

1372
00:55:56,360 --> 00:55:57,360
Open the main door.

1373
00:55:57,740 --> 00:56:01,120
And cross the ballroom holding the fake event spreadsheet under my arm.

1374
00:56:01,120 --> 00:56:02,680
As if it were still real.

1375
00:56:03,100 --> 00:56:04,980
So I looked at me from across the room.

1376
00:56:05,380 --> 00:56:06,040
Did it work?

1377
00:56:06,540 --> 00:56:08,220
She asked with only her mouth.

1378
00:56:08,440 --> 00:56:09,000
It worked.

1379
00:56:09,540 --> 00:56:10,280
She exhaled.

1380
00:56:10,760 --> 00:56:14,960
It was only at that instant that I noticed she'd been holding her breath since Massimo walked

1381
00:56:14,960 --> 00:56:15,940
into the side room.

1382
00:56:16,240 --> 00:56:19,660
The warehouse by the lake was made of galvanized sheet metal.

1383
00:56:20,020 --> 00:56:23,660
Had a rusty sliding gate and smelled of old motor oil.

1384
00:56:24,220 --> 00:56:25,200
I knew the place.

1385
00:56:25,420 --> 00:56:28,240
It had been a family part's depot in the 90s.

1386
00:56:28,540 --> 00:56:30,100
Massimo had never brought me there.

1387
00:56:30,100 --> 00:56:31,920
Now I understood why.

1388
00:56:32,420 --> 00:56:34,420
I went in alone as arranged.

1389
00:56:35,200 --> 00:56:40,980
Dario had stayed 200 meters away in the car with the federal police two turns from there.

1390
00:56:41,320 --> 00:56:45,300
The flash drive of the recording Noelia had just made was in my inner pocket.

1391
00:56:45,780 --> 00:56:51,100
Over my chest, Massimo was in the middle of the warehouse under a single yellow lamp.

1392
00:56:51,580 --> 00:56:54,040
Two armed men, one on each side.

1393
00:56:54,580 --> 00:56:58,100
My mother was tied to a wooden chair three meters from him.

1394
00:56:58,100 --> 00:57:00,580
A live, no bruise in sight.

1395
00:57:01,060 --> 00:57:04,920
Her gaze met mine for a second and I recognized that expression.

1396
00:57:05,500 --> 00:57:08,060
It was the same one she'd had after my father died.

1397
00:57:08,540 --> 00:57:09,120
I'm here.

1398
00:57:09,580 --> 00:57:10,580
Don't do anything stupid.

1399
00:57:11,200 --> 00:57:12,040
You came fast.

1400
00:57:12,700 --> 00:57:14,920
Massimo said, you called me.

1401
00:57:15,060 --> 00:57:16,340
I brought the flash drive.

1402
00:57:16,840 --> 00:57:18,100
I took it out of my pocket.

1403
00:57:18,600 --> 00:57:20,300
I placed it on my open palm.

1404
00:57:20,800 --> 00:57:23,560
Massimo looked at it with his usual tired tenderness.

1405
00:57:23,560 --> 00:57:29,180
And I, for the first time in 20 years saw that tenderness for what it was.

1406
00:57:29,980 --> 00:57:30,640
A machine.

1407
00:57:31,180 --> 00:57:31,840
Break it.

1408
00:57:32,200 --> 00:57:32,460
He said.

1409
00:57:32,860 --> 00:57:35,980
First you say in front of these two men, what you ordered done.

1410
00:57:36,360 --> 00:57:38,400
The two henchmen I'd each other.

1411
00:57:38,960 --> 00:57:40,080
Massimo laughed low.

1412
00:57:40,460 --> 00:57:41,140
Your sentimental.

1413
00:57:42,060 --> 00:57:42,800
I am.

1414
00:57:43,220 --> 00:57:43,840
Say it.

1415
00:57:44,160 --> 00:57:45,140
He sighed.

1416
00:57:45,340 --> 00:57:46,440
He looked at my mother.

1417
00:57:46,880 --> 00:57:47,820
He looked at me.

1418
00:57:48,000 --> 00:57:53,100
He said, with the patience of someone who'd never been contradicted by me in 20 years.

1419
00:57:53,560 --> 00:57:56,980
I killed Antero Cross because he was going to bring the house down.

1420
00:57:57,360 --> 00:58:01,660
I set up the ambush that killed your father because the old Malvani was going soft.

1421
00:58:02,140 --> 00:58:04,520
I raised you because you were more useful alive.

1422
00:58:05,200 --> 00:58:05,460
There.

1423
00:58:06,060 --> 00:58:07,140
Break the flash drive.

1424
00:58:07,740 --> 00:58:09,240
The two henchmen stopped breathing.

1425
00:58:09,740 --> 00:58:12,280
I looked at them long enough for them to see my face.

1426
00:58:12,700 --> 00:58:15,400
And understand that I'd heard the same sentence they had.

1427
00:58:15,780 --> 00:58:17,780
Then I took the ring out of my pants pocket.

1428
00:58:18,320 --> 00:58:21,560
The crest of an eagle with folded wings, old gold.

1429
00:58:21,560 --> 00:58:23,620
Three Melvani generations.

1430
00:58:24,220 --> 00:58:26,620
I set it on top of a crate beside me.

1431
00:58:26,900 --> 00:58:28,140
The Melvani ends here.

1432
00:58:28,460 --> 00:58:30,360
I said, out loud to the two men.

1433
00:58:30,860 --> 00:58:33,060
Whoever stays with me walks out alive.

1434
00:58:33,620 --> 00:58:35,280
Whoever stays with him chooses.

1435
00:58:36,100 --> 00:58:37,400
I knew what I'd just done.

1436
00:58:37,880 --> 00:58:41,380
In two sentences, I dissolved 20 years of structure.

1437
00:58:41,980 --> 00:58:43,120
I felt nothing heroic.

1438
00:58:43,580 --> 00:58:47,940
I felt the way you feel when you sat down a very heavy suitcase you didn't even remember

1439
00:58:47,940 --> 00:58:48,640
you were carrying.

1440
00:58:48,640 --> 00:58:51,900
The two henchmen lowered their guns in half a second.

1441
00:58:52,500 --> 00:58:53,440
That was all.

1442
00:58:53,840 --> 00:58:54,980
Massimo opened his mouth.

1443
00:58:55,460 --> 00:58:56,260
Nothing came out.

1444
00:58:56,700 --> 00:58:58,800
The warehouse door opened from the outside.

1445
00:58:59,460 --> 00:59:01,900
Dario first, federal police behind.

1446
00:59:02,500 --> 00:59:04,840
Massimo raised his hands without needing to be told.

1447
00:59:05,340 --> 00:59:08,760
The man had seen this happen to too many people not to know the choreography.

1448
00:59:09,460 --> 00:59:12,320
My mother closed her eyes for a second and breathed.

1449
00:59:12,420 --> 00:59:13,280
I went to her.

1450
00:59:13,660 --> 00:59:15,980
I untied the rope from her wrist with my hands.

1451
00:59:16,360 --> 00:59:17,420
My hands were shaking.

1452
00:59:17,420 --> 00:59:20,200
I noticed it for the first time in my life.

1453
00:59:20,460 --> 00:59:21,520
You took your time.

1454
00:59:21,900 --> 00:59:22,760
She said quietly.

1455
00:59:23,480 --> 00:59:23,880
I know.

1456
00:59:24,260 --> 00:59:25,240
It wasn't a criticism.

1457
00:59:25,980 --> 00:59:27,580
I pressed my forehead to hers.

1458
00:59:28,040 --> 00:59:28,900
For two seconds.

1459
00:59:29,540 --> 00:59:31,080
Enough for an entire lifetime.

1460
00:59:31,620 --> 00:59:33,420
The flash drive was still in my hand.

1461
00:59:33,840 --> 00:59:35,840
The penthouse was in silence when he arrived.

1462
00:59:36,300 --> 00:59:38,980
I'd turned off all the lights except the living room lamp.

1463
00:59:39,500 --> 00:59:41,140
And Lake Michigan down below.

1464
00:59:41,680 --> 00:59:44,260
looked like a black sheet with small bites of old gold.

1465
00:59:44,780 --> 00:59:46,260
Bruno was in her own mother's apartment.

1466
00:59:46,740 --> 00:59:47,180
Safe.

1467
00:59:47,660 --> 00:59:49,560
With Dario outside since midnight.

1468
00:59:50,160 --> 00:59:52,480
Massimo had been in federal custody since 115.

1469
00:59:53,260 --> 00:59:56,020
I'd turned off my phone after Sorai confirmed it to me.

1470
00:59:56,360 --> 00:59:58,580
Ever and came in through the internal staircase door.

1471
00:59:59,060 --> 01:00:00,200
I looked at his right hand.

1472
01:00:00,680 --> 01:00:01,760
The ring wasn't anywhere.

1473
01:00:02,340 --> 01:00:03,160
You want me to leave.

1474
01:00:03,540 --> 01:00:04,020
He said.

1475
01:00:04,480 --> 01:00:04,760
No.

1476
01:00:05,260 --> 01:00:08,500
He crossed the room slowly and stopped to step away from me.

1477
01:00:08,720 --> 01:00:10,800
There was a little motor oil on his shirt cuff.

1478
01:00:11,140 --> 01:00:13,700
And the mark of the jute rope on the edge of his left hand.

1479
01:00:14,100 --> 01:00:15,740
From where he'd freed his mother's wrist.

1480
01:00:15,740 --> 01:00:18,140
I noticed it before anything else.

1481
01:00:18,400 --> 01:00:24,100
It was the first time in three months that I looked at his hands and didn't see a man who knew

1482
01:00:24,100 --> 01:00:25,240
where the exits were.

1483
01:00:25,600 --> 01:00:28,040
I saw a man who had just freed his mother from a chair.

1484
01:00:28,500 --> 01:00:29,680
I turned everything in.

1485
01:00:29,900 --> 01:00:30,400
He said.

1486
01:00:30,900 --> 01:00:32,260
The police have the flash drive.

1487
01:00:32,680 --> 01:00:33,980
They have your father's tape.

1488
01:00:34,460 --> 01:00:35,280
They have the confession.

1489
01:00:36,020 --> 01:00:37,180
The Melvani is over.

1490
01:00:37,720 --> 01:00:38,220
I know.

1491
01:00:38,540 --> 01:00:39,360
He stayed still.

1492
01:00:39,760 --> 01:00:43,440
And it was only at that instant that I noticed he was waiting for me to take the step.

1493
01:00:43,940 --> 01:00:44,800
For me to choose.

1494
01:00:44,800 --> 01:00:45,660
I did.

1495
01:00:46,300 --> 01:00:47,720
I placed my hand on his chest.

1496
01:00:48,080 --> 01:00:48,900
On the left side.

1497
01:00:49,320 --> 01:00:51,580
Over the inner pocket where the flash drive had been.

1498
01:00:52,040 --> 01:00:54,160
I felt his heartbeat twice against my palm.

1499
01:00:54,660 --> 01:00:55,560
Take off your shirt.

1500
01:00:56,000 --> 01:00:56,680
He didn't laugh.

1501
01:00:57,260 --> 01:00:58,020
He didn't joke.

1502
01:00:58,500 --> 01:01:00,100
He lifted his hand to the first button.

1503
01:01:00,620 --> 01:01:00,880
No.

1504
01:01:01,360 --> 01:01:01,800
I said.

1505
01:01:02,280 --> 01:01:03,020
I'll take it off.

1506
01:01:03,440 --> 01:01:04,740
I started at the second button.

1507
01:01:05,240 --> 01:01:06,340
My fingers weren't shaking.

1508
01:01:06,920 --> 01:01:07,520
Mine weren't.

1509
01:01:08,040 --> 01:01:08,700
His were.

1510
01:01:08,980 --> 01:01:10,580
I'd never seen ever in his hand shake.

1511
01:01:11,040 --> 01:01:13,880
I felt the warmth of his skin before the shirt even fell.

1512
01:01:13,880 --> 01:01:16,440
And that was the first thing that undid me.

1513
01:01:16,720 --> 01:01:19,500
Not his beauty, which I already knew by heart.

1514
01:01:20,000 --> 01:01:20,480
The warmth.

1515
01:01:20,980 --> 01:01:24,000
The realization that he was there, alive, standing.

1516
01:01:24,680 --> 01:01:25,820
Without a family name.

1517
01:01:26,400 --> 01:01:26,660
Mine.

1518
01:01:27,320 --> 01:01:27,880
No, Elia.

1519
01:01:28,440 --> 01:01:29,040
He said, low.

1520
01:01:29,480 --> 01:01:30,100
Don't talk.

1521
01:01:30,620 --> 01:01:32,300
The shirt fell to the living room floor.

1522
01:01:32,820 --> 01:01:34,580
The tattoos on his arms were old.

1523
01:01:35,020 --> 01:01:36,340
With no crest at all.

1524
01:01:36,600 --> 01:01:37,780
I already knew them.

1525
01:01:38,000 --> 01:01:39,980
But that night they seemed like something else.

1526
01:01:40,340 --> 01:01:41,920
They seemed for the first time.

1527
01:01:42,360 --> 01:01:42,960
Only his.

1528
01:01:42,960 --> 01:01:47,300
He picked me up with the calm urgency of a man who'd spent the whole night holding

1529
01:01:47,300 --> 01:01:51,260
his captive mother, holding his own father dead for 20 years,

1530
01:01:51,580 --> 01:01:53,640
holding a ring that weighed three generations.

1531
01:01:54,320 --> 01:01:56,620
And now didn't want to hold anything other than me.

1532
01:01:56,880 --> 01:01:58,520
He crossed the room toward the bedroom.

1533
01:01:59,100 --> 01:02:02,940
I pressed my mouth to the side of his neck and felt his pulse beat against my lips.

1534
01:02:03,440 --> 01:02:05,400
It was the same rhythm as months before.

1535
01:02:05,900 --> 01:02:06,940
On the hotel balcony.

1536
01:02:07,620 --> 01:02:08,400
Faster now.

1537
01:02:08,760 --> 01:02:09,540
Not from fear.

1538
01:02:10,080 --> 01:02:10,780
From choice.

1539
01:02:10,780 --> 01:02:12,720
He laid me on the bed carefully.

1540
01:02:13,460 --> 01:02:16,460
He stayed on top of me, holding his own weight on his arms.

1541
01:02:16,960 --> 01:02:18,240
Without covering me yet.

1542
01:02:18,540 --> 01:02:20,480
There was a small cut above his left eyebrow.

1543
01:02:21,020 --> 01:02:22,340
It must have been at the warehouse.

1544
01:02:22,920 --> 01:02:24,460
I pressed my thumb to it.

1545
01:02:24,680 --> 01:02:25,260
Did it hurt?

1546
01:02:25,800 --> 01:02:26,080
No.

1547
01:02:26,640 --> 01:02:27,540
Does it hurt now?

1548
01:02:28,020 --> 01:02:28,340
No.

1549
01:02:28,800 --> 01:02:30,160
He lowered his mouth to mine.

1550
01:02:30,540 --> 01:02:31,880
It wasn't a beginning kiss.

1551
01:02:32,300 --> 01:02:33,860
It was a continuation kiss.

1552
01:02:34,280 --> 01:02:36,200
As if it had started three months earlier.

1553
01:02:36,720 --> 01:02:37,300
