1819
01:12:18,220 --> 01:12:19,460
She laughed before I finished.

1820
01:12:20,060 --> 01:12:21,220
The ceremony was small.

1821
01:12:21,740 --> 01:12:22,820
Twenty odd people.

1822
01:12:23,180 --> 01:12:27,380
Bruno sat in the first row in the beige dress that had belonged to her mother at a wedding in

1823
01:12:27,380 --> 01:12:28,840
Sicily 60 years earlier.

1824
01:12:29,220 --> 01:12:31,880
She'd told the story three times at the dinner the night before.

1825
01:12:32,360 --> 01:12:33,540
And gotten teary-eyed all.

1826
01:12:33,540 --> 01:12:34,300
Three.

1827
01:12:34,920 --> 01:12:37,440
Tisha Rome, at the back, discreet.

1828
01:12:38,000 --> 01:12:40,660
Her hair now short and her eyes without any makeup.

1829
01:12:41,220 --> 01:12:43,700
She'd testified against Calvin seven months earlier.

1830
01:12:44,220 --> 01:12:46,240
Had moved to another city for three months.

1831
01:12:46,740 --> 01:12:47,980
It'd come back a different woman.

1832
01:12:48,420 --> 01:12:50,940
She'd sent a note the week before asking to be there.

1833
01:12:51,180 --> 01:12:53,000
I said yes without needing to think.

1834
01:12:53,560 --> 01:12:55,120
Calvin wasn't mentioned by anyone.

1835
01:12:55,580 --> 01:12:59,380
He'd been convicted months earlier to six years for the campaign and bezelmen.

1836
01:12:59,660 --> 01:13:02,260
Plus more things that turned up after the first stone rolled.

1837
01:13:02,260 --> 01:13:06,480
I'd seen the headline on an airport bench once, coming back from San Francisco.

1838
01:13:07,140 --> 01:13:08,180
I looked for two seconds.

1839
01:13:08,720 --> 01:13:09,480
I kept walking.

1840
01:13:10,080 --> 01:13:11,580
Everand was on the other side of the balcony.

1841
01:13:12,220 --> 01:13:15,400
Black suit, no tie, no ring on his right finger.

1842
01:13:15,880 --> 01:13:18,400
He'd never put another ring there since the night at the warehouse.

1843
01:13:18,920 --> 01:13:23,040
He'd said the week before that he was going to put the wedding band on the left,

1844
01:13:23,460 --> 01:13:25,660
and that that was already enough for an entire lifetime.

1845
01:13:26,200 --> 01:13:26,860
I didn't argue.

1846
01:13:27,440 --> 01:13:28,680
Dario was beside him.

1847
01:13:28,940 --> 01:13:29,920
Black suit too.

1848
01:13:30,280 --> 01:13:30,880
Black tie.

1849
01:13:30,880 --> 01:13:33,220
Neutral expression as always.

1850
01:13:33,680 --> 01:13:34,760
Surai nudged my elbow.

1851
01:13:35,320 --> 01:13:35,960
Look at him.

1852
01:13:36,260 --> 01:13:37,140
She whispered.

1853
01:13:37,400 --> 01:13:39,060
Dressed just like the cemetery suit.

1854
01:13:39,720 --> 01:13:40,120
Surai.

1855
01:13:40,580 --> 01:13:42,920
A poorly wrapped problem is hereditary noelia.

1856
01:13:43,540 --> 01:13:45,560
I pressed my lips together so I wouldn't laugh.

1857
01:13:46,080 --> 01:13:47,700
She pressed hers together too.

1858
01:13:47,940 --> 01:13:51,740
For two seconds, the two of us looked like two teenagers in a school line.

1859
01:13:52,180 --> 01:13:54,280
Holding back the laugh with our hands over our mouths.

1860
01:13:54,760 --> 01:13:56,000
I walked over to Everand.

1861
01:13:56,440 --> 01:13:57,620
He hadn't moved his face.

1862
01:13:58,020 --> 01:14:00,060
But I saw, when I got close,

1863
01:14:00,060 --> 01:14:02,900
his pulse beat twice as hard on the side of his neck.

1864
01:14:03,400 --> 01:14:05,300
I'd known how to read that in him for years.

1865
01:14:05,760 --> 01:14:07,060
The one sign he couldn't control.

1866
01:14:07,620 --> 01:14:08,480
His vow was short.

1867
01:14:08,900 --> 01:14:10,360
I'd asked him not to write much.

1868
01:14:10,840 --> 01:14:11,420
He complied.

1869
01:14:11,940 --> 01:14:14,480
I promised on the balcony where we're standing a year ago

1870
01:14:14,480 --> 01:14:15,900
that I wouldn't lie to you anymore.

1871
01:14:16,380 --> 01:14:17,320
I kept it.

1872
01:14:17,560 --> 01:14:18,580
I'll keep keeping it.

1873
01:14:18,760 --> 01:14:19,320
That's all.

1874
01:14:19,640 --> 01:14:20,380
That was everything.

1875
01:14:20,980 --> 01:14:21,980
Mine was a little longer.

1876
01:14:22,560 --> 01:14:23,020
Not much.

1877
01:14:23,540 --> 01:14:27,020
I arrived at this hotel one night believing I'd hired an escort by mistake.

1878
01:14:27,500 --> 01:14:29,880
I left believing I'd made a mistake that would cost me

1879
01:14:29,880 --> 01:14:35,680
it took me three months to understand I'd made a mistake in a way that had given me everything back.

1880
01:14:36,020 --> 01:14:36,900
I looked at him.

1881
01:14:37,180 --> 01:14:40,960
The night the hotel's big screen decided for us was the luckiest night of my life.

1882
01:14:41,200 --> 01:14:42,520
I just didn't know it yet.

1883
01:14:42,800 --> 01:14:44,320
He lowered his head for half a second.

1884
01:14:44,840 --> 01:14:46,120
I saw his cheek go darker.

1885
01:14:46,820 --> 01:14:50,260
Bruna in the first row brought a handkerchief to her eyes.

1886
01:14:50,760 --> 01:14:51,600
Surrised sniffled.

1887
01:14:51,980 --> 01:14:54,800
Dario tightened his tie with two fingers and let go slowly.

1888
01:14:55,400 --> 01:14:56,580
The judge said the line.

1889
01:14:57,040 --> 01:14:58,000
Everand kissed me.

1890
01:14:58,000 --> 01:14:59,580
It was a simple kiss.

1891
01:15:00,020 --> 01:15:00,280
Calm.

1892
01:15:00,840 --> 01:15:02,160
With no hurry at all.

1893
01:15:02,420 --> 01:15:03,100
No one to beat.

1894
01:15:03,260 --> 01:15:04,200
Nothing to prove.

1895
01:15:04,760 --> 01:15:07,020
Surrised whispered in my ear when I went back to the row.

1896
01:15:07,560 --> 01:15:07,740
There.

1897
01:15:08,300 --> 01:15:10,160
Now you're a poorly wrapped problem too.

1898
01:15:10,520 --> 01:15:11,080
I laughed.

1899
01:15:11,600 --> 01:15:12,780
This time I laughed first.

1900
01:15:13,300 --> 01:15:15,780
We bought the house on the lake in our fifth year of marriage.

1901
01:15:16,060 --> 01:15:20,840
It had a large living room with a high ceiling and light that came in until the middle of the afternoon.

1902
01:15:21,460 --> 01:15:25,680
A kitchen with a window facing the water where the smell of coffee always mixed with the smell

1903
01:15:25,680 --> 01:15:27,400
of wet grass coming from the garden.

1904
01:15:27,400 --> 01:15:31,060
And two small bedrooms upstairs, side by side.

1905
01:15:31,600 --> 01:15:32,860
We're before nothing had lived.

1906
01:15:33,320 --> 01:15:34,400
Now too lived there.

1907
01:15:34,800 --> 01:15:37,820
The girl was four years old and had her father's eyes.

1908
01:15:38,220 --> 01:15:39,400
Dark, attentive.

1909
01:15:39,980 --> 01:15:42,380
The kind that noticed everything before asking anything.

1910
01:15:42,840 --> 01:15:45,600
The boy was too and had my father's laugh.

1911
01:15:45,920 --> 01:15:49,540
Something I didn't know he'd inherited until he laughed for the first time in the bath.

1912
01:15:49,900 --> 01:15:52,600
It was the laugh I hadn't heard since I was seven years old.

1913
01:15:52,860 --> 01:15:55,340
I stood there with the towel in my hand too long.

1914
01:15:55,340 --> 01:15:58,080
And everyone appeared in the doorway and looked at me.

1915
01:15:58,300 --> 01:15:59,240
And didn't ask anything.

1916
01:15:59,840 --> 01:16:01,500
And stayed there until I breathed again.

1917
01:16:01,980 --> 01:16:04,360
The events company had opened in the second year.

1918
01:16:04,640 --> 01:16:07,940
I'd named it in my father's honor without telling anyone it was an honor.

1919
01:16:08,420 --> 01:16:09,380
Only Sarai knew.

1920
01:16:09,740 --> 01:16:10,140
And everyone.

1921
01:16:10,800 --> 01:16:16,200
The first client was a 42-year-old woman who had been left at the altar at the Hilton in Houston three months earlier.

1922
01:16:16,740 --> 01:16:18,280
I organized her birthday party.

1923
01:16:18,800 --> 01:16:19,680
300 people.

1924
01:16:20,180 --> 01:16:23,480
She danced all night with her shoes in her hand from midnight on.

1925
01:16:23,480 --> 01:16:25,900
At the end she hugged me at the door and said,

1926
01:16:26,160 --> 01:16:27,360
How did you know what I needed?

1927
01:16:27,820 --> 01:16:29,320
I said, I knew.

1928
01:16:29,720 --> 01:16:31,340
She didn't ask anything else.

1929
01:16:31,800 --> 01:16:34,680
Sarai was a partner, officially, from the third year on.

1930
01:16:35,060 --> 01:16:37,640
Dario showed up at the office with suspicious frequency,

1931
01:16:38,380 --> 01:16:40,800
always with coffee from the bakery Sarai liked,

1932
01:16:41,220 --> 01:16:43,120
and the two still pretended no one noticed.

1933
01:16:44,340 --> 01:16:46,720
Sarai said it had been the worst mistake of her life,

1934
01:16:46,960 --> 01:16:48,440
and the only one she'd make again.

1935
01:16:49,500 --> 01:16:51,320
Dario answered with a half expression.

1936
01:16:52,160 --> 01:16:53,840
She filed the smile away.

1937
01:16:54,380 --> 01:16:56,040
She always filed it away.

1938
01:16:57,180 --> 01:16:59,600
If Ren managed to completely legal operations,

1939
01:17:00,340 --> 01:17:01,800
one in hospitality in Chicago,

1940
01:17:02,440 --> 01:17:04,120
another in freight transport in Detroit.

1941
01:17:05,100 --> 01:17:06,940
There was no one calling him sir anymore.

1942
01:17:07,880 --> 01:17:11,700
There was no one waiting for him to decide something without asking his wife first.

1943
01:17:11,880 --> 01:17:13,000
He used to say,

1944
01:17:13,240 --> 01:17:15,560
When the new partners asked how he'd learned to delegate,

1945
01:17:16,160 --> 01:17:19,860
that it had been the hard way, no one understood, I understood.

1946
01:17:19,860 --> 01:17:24,340
The garden in late spring turned green nearly yellow in the late afternoon.

1947
01:17:24,940 --> 01:17:27,000
I was sitting on the wooden step of the deck.

1948
01:17:27,280 --> 01:17:30,720
My bare feet against the grass still damp from the morning sprinkler,

1949
01:17:31,220 --> 01:17:34,000
and I watched the two of them run around the bucket of water

1950
01:17:34,000 --> 01:17:35,680
and Oliya had filled at lunchtime.

1951
01:17:36,080 --> 01:17:37,440
The girl always won.

1952
01:17:37,880 --> 01:17:39,380
The boy laughed even losing.

1953
01:17:39,900 --> 01:17:43,860
At some moments she'd come back to push him lightly before continuing to run,

1954
01:17:44,140 --> 01:17:46,400
and he'd laugh again, and they'd keep going,

1955
01:17:46,700 --> 01:17:48,500
and the sequence repeated in a loop,

1956
01:17:48,500 --> 01:17:52,720
as if that garden were the only place in the world where it made sense to stay,

1957
01:17:53,360 --> 01:17:55,740
I thought without warning, of my father.

1958
01:17:56,300 --> 01:18:00,440
Not of what he'd been, of what he would have been if Masimo hadn't decided otherwise.

1959
01:18:01,040 --> 01:18:02,220
20 odd years earlier.

1960
01:18:02,840 --> 01:18:04,260
I thought of on Tero too.

1961
01:18:04,500 --> 01:18:07,160
I thought of him many times in the last seven years.

1962
01:18:07,600 --> 01:18:10,180
It was the first time I'd thought of him without wait,

1963
01:18:10,740 --> 01:18:11,560
only with gratitude.

1964
01:18:12,180 --> 01:18:14,600
I thought of the old Malvani for half a second.

1965
01:18:14,940 --> 01:18:16,600
I thought of Masimo for less.

1966
01:18:16,600 --> 01:18:19,380
The two of them were in the same place now.

1967
01:18:19,660 --> 01:18:23,540
In packages I'd stored in some compartment of my head and locked with a key.

1968
01:18:23,860 --> 01:18:26,860
Not to forget, so I wouldn't have to open it every day.

1969
01:18:27,220 --> 01:18:28,620
The girl fell in the grass.

1970
01:18:29,100 --> 01:18:31,100
She got up without crying, she kept running.

1971
01:18:31,420 --> 01:18:36,600
I'd spent the first 36 years of my life believing that being seen was being exposed.

1972
01:18:37,200 --> 01:18:39,480
That a man standing didn't lower his guard.

1973
01:18:39,980 --> 01:18:43,700
That sentiment was the first thing the enemy used to take you down.

1974
01:18:43,700 --> 01:18:48,200
That woman had walked into the hotel one night thinking she was hiring an accessory.

1975
01:18:48,600 --> 01:18:51,020
Had looked me in the eye without knowing who I was,

1976
01:18:51,300 --> 01:18:53,580
and had kept looking at me after finding out.

1977
01:18:53,920 --> 01:18:58,540
It was the only thing in my entire life that had taught me the opposite.

1978
01:18:59,040 --> 01:19:01,840
Being seen without lying was the only way to be loved.

1979
01:19:02,340 --> 01:19:05,960
It had taken me almost 40 years to understand a sentence of eight words.

1980
01:19:06,480 --> 01:19:08,860
I smelled the coffee before I turned my head.

1981
01:19:09,280 --> 01:19:10,980
I crossed the garden with two cups.

1982
01:19:10,980 --> 01:19:14,400
The one on the left had sugar, the one on the right didn't.

1983
01:19:14,680 --> 01:19:15,740
I never switched them.

1984
01:19:16,040 --> 01:19:19,780
In seven years I hadn't switched ones, and he'd never asked me to switch.

1985
01:19:20,280 --> 01:19:21,680
I sat beside him on the step.

1986
01:19:22,160 --> 01:19:24,140
The wood was warm from the afternoon sun.

1987
01:19:24,540 --> 01:19:26,020
I held out the one without sugar.

1988
01:19:26,520 --> 01:19:28,280
He accepted it without looking at the cup.

1989
01:19:28,540 --> 01:19:31,200
He looked at me first, as he always did,

1990
01:19:31,620 --> 01:19:34,780
as if I were the most important information before anything else.

1991
01:19:35,100 --> 01:19:36,620
They're going to sleep in the car today.

1992
01:19:37,100 --> 01:19:38,880
I said, they always sleep.

1993
01:19:39,400 --> 01:19:40,320
The girl fell again.

1994
01:19:40,320 --> 01:19:41,740
She got up again.

1995
01:19:42,220 --> 01:19:44,380
Shook the dirt off her knee with two efficient slaps.

1996
01:19:44,960 --> 01:19:46,540
The boy sat in the middle of the grass.

1997
01:19:46,980 --> 01:19:51,440
Decided he was tired, and started pulling up toughs with the tranquil patients of someone who

1998
01:19:51,440 --> 01:19:53,120
had the rest of his life to do it.

1999
01:19:53,300 --> 01:19:55,280
I leaned my shoulder against a vr. shoulder.

2000
01:19:55,740 --> 01:19:57,300
He leaned his shoulder against mine.

2001
01:19:57,680 --> 01:19:59,620
It was the oldest gesture in our house.

2002
01:19:59,900 --> 01:20:01,080
Older than the house.

2003
01:20:01,340 --> 01:20:04,860
I'd learned it from him on the penthouse balcony in the third month.

2004
01:20:05,240 --> 01:20:09,000
On a night when I didn't want to talk, and he hadn't insisted on talking.

2005
01:20:09,000 --> 01:20:11,900
We'd stayed like that, shoulder to shoulder,

2006
01:20:12,560 --> 01:20:13,880
until the sky brightened.

2007
01:20:14,200 --> 01:20:14,880
I took a sip.

2008
01:20:15,360 --> 01:20:17,580
The coffee was strong, a little bitter,

2009
01:20:18,160 --> 01:20:19,620
exactly the way I liked it.

2010
01:20:19,880 --> 01:20:24,800
I thought, without meaning to, of a sentence I'd said to myself seven years earlier,

2011
01:20:25,240 --> 01:20:28,240
in a low voice, at the entrance of my old department.

2012
01:20:28,860 --> 01:20:30,400
The morning after the first kiss,

2013
01:20:30,660 --> 01:20:35,100
I'd said it was strange to know so little of the past of someone I'd just chosen to believe in.

2014
01:20:35,380 --> 01:20:36,400
Now I knew everything.

2015
01:20:36,400 --> 01:20:38,760
I'd known too soon afterward,

2016
01:20:39,320 --> 01:20:42,440
and it had hurt more than anything before, but I knew.

2017
01:20:42,940 --> 01:20:44,760
And knowing hadn't undone the choice.

2018
01:20:45,260 --> 01:20:46,500
It had sustained it.

2019
01:20:46,720 --> 01:20:50,080
I watched the boy pulling up grass with the concentration of a scientist.

2020
01:20:50,660 --> 01:20:53,180
I watched the girl counting her own steps out loud.

2021
01:20:53,800 --> 01:20:55,180
Four, five, six.

2022
01:20:55,720 --> 01:20:57,240
Always starting over at seven.

2023
01:20:57,700 --> 01:20:59,400
I looked at the lake at the end of the garden.

2024
01:20:59,920 --> 01:21:03,600
It's silvery surface against the sky that was starting to turn orange at the edges.

2025
01:21:03,600 --> 01:21:06,360
The kind of color that lasted a short time,

2026
01:21:06,700 --> 01:21:08,300
and that you only saw when you were looking.

2027
01:21:08,920 --> 01:21:11,680
Dignity, I thought, wasn't never falling.

2028
01:21:12,280 --> 01:21:13,100
I had fallen.

2029
01:21:13,620 --> 01:21:15,940
I'd fallen at the altar at 20 odd years old,

2030
01:21:16,260 --> 01:21:19,820
before 200 people who preferred to pity me, then to defend me.

2031
01:21:20,000 --> 01:21:24,060
I'd fallen again in the hotel ballroom three months after the first kiss.

2032
01:21:24,340 --> 01:21:27,280
When I heard my father's voice come out of a 20-year-old tape,

2033
01:21:27,720 --> 01:21:29,700
I'd fallen every time I needed to fall,

2034
01:21:30,020 --> 01:21:32,260
and gotten up without asking permission for it.

2035
01:21:32,260 --> 01:21:36,360
Dignity was getting up and building a house where pain had no way in.

2036
01:21:36,620 --> 01:21:37,620
The house was all around.

2037
01:21:38,240 --> 01:21:39,340
The children were in the garden.

2038
01:21:39,900 --> 01:21:41,020
The man was at my side.

2039
01:21:41,460 --> 01:21:42,760
His shoulder against mine.

2040
01:21:43,100 --> 01:21:45,220
With no family rang at all on his finger,

2041
01:21:45,760 --> 01:21:47,520
holding a cup of coffee without sugar,

2042
01:21:48,080 --> 01:21:50,880
as if it were the simplest and most certain thing in the world.

2043
01:21:51,260 --> 01:21:53,600
I took the second sip, and I smiled.
